name: Wendy Ditoro
description: Meet Wendy : My real estate business mission is to be a partner in your largest purchase with A Client First Focus.  This Client First Focus builds a unique strategy to partner with you on your home selling and home purchase.  I will work with you to create and wrap around individualized pricing strategies, marketing strategies, purchase strategies and investment strategies that are created to meet your personal goals. Wondering when you should call?  Are you beginning to think about selling or purchasing but not sure if you will be ready this year or next year?   Unsure what you can afford or the best approach to begin the process to sell? Don’t worry, call me.  The best time to meet is NOW.  The value of working with me is the resources and education I can provide to you BEFORE you are ready to sell a home or purchase a home.  Don’t waste your money or your time, meet me for coffee or tea and we will discuss your home dreams and set a path to get you there! Selling Your Property Selling your property is one of the biggest decisions you will make in your life.  I believe in meeting with each client to determine what you want from your sale.  How can I help you get it and how can we create a winning team to get you there?  I will partner with you to create a listing and marketing strategy to sell your home that works for you and your lifestyle.  We will have honest conversations and you will receive specific guidance on how to position yourself best in the current market. Purchasing a Home It doesn’t matter how young or how old you are, purchasing a home can be stressful and scary.  I would love to hear your plans and see how I can help you purchase your next home.  Most people considering to purchase are surprised at what they truly can afford.  Barriers such as credit scores, down payments and monthly payments often keep people from acting on purchasing a property or a dream home.  Are you unsure?  Don’t be, call me to schedule a meeting to discuss your purchasing plans and I can provide you with the next steps to get you there. Want to Build a Home? Have you considered building a home?  Do you get overwhelmed with the idea?  Work with an agent that has built their own home and help many others through the process.  Unsure which builder is best for your or where you want to build.  Many builders have agents that are provided incentives by the builders to sell that builders home.  While they are very capable agents, find an agent that understands and has been involved in the build process. An agent that is impartial and familiar with All Builders and has your best interest during the building process is crucial.

name: Haley Walker
description: I am as genuinely passionate about your real estate search as you are. I understand that as a customer you are placing your faith in me to turn the enchanting allure of buying or selling a home into a gleaming reality. Rest assured, whichever your need may be, you are in great hands. From the initial meeting until the day you exchange keys, as an energetic agent I will provide you with uncompromising service, guidance and diligence. I will work with you on each and every detail, making sure to consistently exceed your expectations. For buyers, as a native Nebraskan I take great pride in custom designing each and every search to reflect the visions and individuality of my customers. I will give you my full attention, as I truly share your desire for finding the perfect home at the ideal price. Sellers benefit from my energy, devotion and comprehensive background in marketing. I will creatively develop and implement marketing strategies to award my clients properties with maximum and diversified exposure. Whatever your residential real estate needs may be, it is with open arms that I would welcome you to work with me.

name: Joni Friberg
description: Joni (Grunewald) Friberg was raised in Cass County, NE and graduated from Conestoga High School. In keeping with her family’s tradition of military service, she joined ROTC at the University of Nebraska at Omaha. Upon graduating from UNO with a BA, she started her Air Force career in public affairs and went on to complete her MBA from the University of Phoenix. Joni has over 22 years of experience in marketing, public relations, sales, and technology. From her time in the Air Force to her years as an Executive Casino Host, her rich and diverse career path has taken her around the world. She’s able to fully embrace and communicate with people from every walk of life, culture and at every stage of their journey.

name: Kourtney Terry
description: Kourtney's work ethic and foundation built on helping others are what make her a great resource for all your real estate needs. She has several years of experience in property management, customer service, and construction management. She is a very valuable resource for those looking to buy, sell, or invest in real estate. Her passion for real estate started when she was a first-time home buyer and realized the importance of having a good agent who goes above and beyond for their client. Kourtney aims to leave a lasting positive impression on those she helps along the way. She is personable, compassionate, and feels most accomplished when helping others succeed and fulfill their dreams.

name: Britney Boltinghouse
description: Welcome to my business page. As an agent representing one of the most dynamic real estate brands in the country, you can expect the utmost professionalism and dedication to all of your real estate needs. From our very first meeting to the final closing, I'm here to provide you with best-in-class service to help you buy or sell a home. Equipped with the finest tools and technology, I'll guide you through the real estate transaction, every step of the way. Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices . . . Good to Know®

name: Margaret VonTersch
description: Welcome Building Client Relationships for Life, One House at a Time! You don’t need a real estate agent every day. When you do need an agent, you need an agent you can trust and rely on to guide you through a major change. Whether you are purchasing or building your first home, selling your family home or relocating, you need an agent who will stand as your advisor through one of life’s major changes. The Margaret Von Tersch Difference As your agent, you can rely on me to: Guide you through the evolving real estate market Communicate openly with you Listen to your needs Understand your real estate objections Help you achieve your goals by taking the time to understand them I am grateful for the opportunity to meet and work with people during a milestone in their lives. Call me today or when you need a trusted real estate advisor and advocate. Isn't it nice to know you have a friend in the real estate business?

name: Lisa Andrews
description: : I have over 25 years of experience working on behalf of clients. Let my experience make yours a great one! I make what's important to you, important to me. I'll work in your best interest, and I'll make your next move my top priority. Licensed Realtor BS University of Nebraska Omaha National Association of Realtors Nebraska Realtors Association Omaha Area Board of Realtors REALTOR®, PSA, SRES® Great Plains Multiple Listing Service Sales at Every Price Point Throughout the Metro Multiple Top Producer Awards Community Volunteer What to Expect: HONESTY & TRANSPARENCY INTEGRITY RESPECT TIMELY & REACHABLE ACTING IN YOUR BEST INTEREST

name: Mallory Young
description: As a Nebraska native and a licensed real estate professional with Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate, I recognize and value the trust my clients place in me, and I strive every day to exceed their expectations. As a long time resident of the Omaha area I will lead you in the right direction while explaining every step of the way! I will keep my clients updated on market trends and keep an open line of communication day or night. My goal is to make your real estate dreams a reality!

name: Christina Reinig
description: My name is Christina Reinig and I have a passion for helping people. My first vocation was as a teacher and then a gifted facilitator at Gretna High School for over 19 years. There I learned to engage the students and helped them achieve their goals and taught problem-solving techniques. As I transitioned into real estate, I found the same skills I learned as a teacher applies to real estate. I build a trustworthy relationship with all my clients and I feel that it is the most important part of my success. Nothing means more to me than when my clients trust me and share my name with their family and friends. I am very passionate about my work. My phone is never off and I am always available to answer questions. I couldn't do this if it wasn't for my family, especially my loving husband of 41 years.­ I have been honored to receive "Rookie of the Year" award in 2006 and was voted by my peers as the "Outstanding Ambassador of the Year" in 2009. I also received Top Individual award for 2011 and 2012 while at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices.­ Over 20 years of being a Leading Edge or President's Circle relating to multi-million dollar sales. It isn't about selling the homes but about the people. I would count it a privilege to be your personal agent in the buying and selling process. I look forward to EVERYDAY being a new day in the real estate world. Just give me a call or text at 402-677-7099 or send me any email at christina.reinig2@gmail.com

name: Julie Sweet
description: What Season of Life are You In? Whether you're considering downsizing now or in the future, you’ve outgrown your current home, you’re ready for your first home or you’re somewhere in between, I would be happy to help. As a business owner of 15 years, I am resourceful, highly organized and committed to excellent customer service. I have 35 years of marketing, customer service & public relations experience. I am highly detail-oriented, relieving my buyers and sellers of much of the work involved in a typical real estate transaction. I am far more committed to providing exceptional service for a few buyers and sellers at a time than I am in being a "top producer." I truly have a heart for people, am a long-hauler & match pace with my sellers & buyers without pressure.  If you’re looking for a Realtor who will help you think through your options & answer your questions from start to finish, I am Your Realtor for All Your Seasons of Life.

name: Lyndsey Golden
description: As a real estate professional at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate, I understand the importance of working with an agent who will have your best interests at heart. That is why I believe in customer service above all else and believing that every individual deserves my full commitment and loyalty. I am supported by a company that understands the customer's needs in a dynamic and rapidly changing real estate environment. This enables me to offer the most powerful real estate services to home buyers and sellers, which includes relocation services, financing, title insurance, and much more. Lyndsey Golden • 402-650-7010 • lyndsey.golden@bhhsamb.com

name: Kathy Lanphier
description: Kathy has been a licensed real estate agent for more than 20 years now. Many of those years were spent as a Domestic and International Corporate Relocation specialist. As a well-connected professional within the Omaha business community, she has her finger on the pulse of local corporations. Kathy is truly at her best when there are multiple balls in the air and she can alleviate stress for her client, helping them make clear decisions. With a father who was a farmer and mother who was a schoolteacher, she learned what grit, perseverance and hard work were at a very early age. Not many realtors take on the roles of organizer, stager, photographer, handyman, therapist, housekeeper, painter, tour guide, savvy marketer and keen negotiator, but Kathy does it all. Give her the challenge and she will bring you the result. "I consistently surprise people with an innate ability to make good things happen. I pay attention to every detail and will stand behind you every step of the way, developing a relationship of trust through knowledge, patience and good humor. I ensure that the process of negotiating the logistical, emotional and financial hurdles of your transaction will be made as easy as possible." – Kathy Lanphier

name: Houfek Realty Group Houfek Realty Group
Ashima Choudhary
description: Meet Ashima Energetic. Passionate. Knowledgeable. ‘Open, honest communication is the best foundation for any relationship, but remember that at the end of the day it’s not what you say or what you do, but how you make people feel that matters the most.” - Tony Hsieh, CEO of Zappos Ashima Choudhary loves working with people.  She brings her creativity, enthusiasm and sharp attention to detail to help buyers search for their new house that matches their needs and help sellers get the most value for their home.  Ashima is known for her integrity and sincerity in all her dealings. “I will listen to you!” Buying and selling can oftentimes be a stressful process but it does not need to be.  Ashima is an excellent communicator and she will spend as much time as you need to explain each part of the process in detail. She will work hard to lower your stress to make the experience as enjoyable as possible. “I am not #1, but you are my #1 priority!” Ashima will be an advocate for you to help you save time and money.  She has decades of experience working for her clients at her prior enterprises - whether it be in helping with their complicated banking needs or be as simple as helping them board a flight.  She was rated top customer service agent for her ability to listen to her clients and solve their problems. “I believe that building relationships is far more important than business” Ashima Choudhary was born and raised in India to a military family.  She moved to Omaha from California in 2008 and has not looked back.  She loves Omaha’s Midwest family-oriented culture and its friendly people. When Ashima is not helping client, she is busy shuttling her two boys to their activities and keeping her husband out of trouble!  She loves to try new restaurants and cuisines.  She also loves to travel both within our wonderful country and internationally.  She is an avid dancer and loves to work out. Please call me or email me if you have any real estate related questions - even if you are not ready to buy or sell today. "Strive not to be a success, but rather to be of value." - Albert Einstein Your Referral is the Best Compliment I can Earn !!!

name: Aaron S Krier
description: My name is Aaron and I am a full service realtor who specializes in the greater Omaha and Council Bluffs areas.  I strive to do what's best for my clients while always keeping their wants and needs as my top priority. I own several investment properties of my own, and enjoy sharing my knowledge with those interested in investing in real estate for their retirement. My work ethic and real estate knowledge result in elated clients and long-lasting relationships. Handing the keys to a buyer that has purchased their dream home or seeing a seller walk from a closing table satisfied is what I live for. My ability to see the big picture for my clients has aided them in consistently having smooth transactions. I look forward to encountering new clients, and helping them to navigate their specific situation and challenges.

name: Jenna Friesen
description: Your Trusted Realtor and Interior Designer Are you feeling overwhelmed by the complexities of buying or selling a home? Look no further! I'm Jenna Friesen, a seasoned realtor and experienced interior designer, here to simplify the process for you. With a deep understanding of the Omaha real estate market, I specialize in helping clients navigate their unique circumstances and find their ideal homes. As a recipient of the prestigious 2021 President's Circle award and a nominee for New Ambassador of the Year in 2023, my dedication to excellence is evident. I take pride in the many 5-star reviews from satisfied clients, who have entrusted me with their real estate journeys. Whether you're looking to downsize, upgrade, relocate within the town, or venture beyond state lines, I will guide you toward the best options for you and your family. With a track record of success, including the 2022 Leading Edge Society award from BHHS and a nomination for Rookie of the Year in 2020, I have helped numerous families turn their dreams of homeownership into reality. My expertise in both real estate and interior design ensures that you'll receive comprehensive guidance and personalized solutions every step of the way. Let's work together to make your next move a seamless and fulfilling experience. Contact me today, and let's embark on this exciting journey of finding your perfect home. ____________________________________ Omaha is a thriving city that combines a rich history with modern amenities and a strong economy. With its affordable housing options, steady job growth, and a friendly community, Omaha has become an attractive destination for investors seeking long-term returns. Whether you're interested in residential or commercial properties, Omaha has a diverse range of options to suit your investment strategy. As a local real estate agent, I have an in-depth understanding of the Omaha market, keeping up with the latest trends and developments. I can guide you through the entire investment process, from finding properties with excellent potential to negotiating favorable deals. My goal is to ensure you make informed decisions and maximize your returns. In addition to my expertise in real estate, I also offer interior designing services. Whether you're looking to enhance the aesthetic appeal of your investment property or want to stage it for sale, I can help you create a visually stunning and functional space. With my eye for design and knowledge of current trends, I can transform your property into a standout investment. Investing in Omaha real estate is a smart choice due to the city's steady growth, strong rental demand, and favorable economic conditions. Let me, Jenna Friesen, be your trusted partner in this exciting journey. Together, we can navigate the Omaha market, find lucrative opportunities, and create spaces that attract both tenants and buyers.

name: Cindy Cawley
description: Cindy Cawley is a full-time real estate agent with 28 years of experience selling homes and condominiums in the luxury market in Omaha, Nebraska. Born and raised in Omaha, she graduated from Creighton University with a teaching degree. She has helped hundreds of homeowners buy and sell their homes in Omaha and all surrounding areas -- executive homes, condominiums, lake homes, acreages, downtown and midtown condos and townhouses, villas, first-time homeowners, and those new to the Omaha area. Specilizing in District 66/Westside, Regency, Rockbrook,  Linden Estates, The Sanctuary, The Ridges, Five Fountains, Baywood, Fairacres, Dundee, Happy Hollow Country Club area, Aksarben, and Memorial Park and downton Omaha, Elkhorn, Millard, Bennington, and Lincoln homes. As a former teacher, Cindy has a vast knowledge of the private and public school systems in the Omaha area. When asked why she chose real estate as a career, she always mentions her job is teaching clients the process of buying and selling a home. Cindy has helped countless physicians and their families relocating to area hospitals / medical centers. In addition to being a relocation specialist, her passion for having happy customers has always been her top priority. She possesses the qualities buyers and sellers want with their agent. Listening closely to her clients and matching their wants and needs has resulted in Cindy Cawley being one of the city's top real estate agents year after year.  Many of her clients are repeat customers who have trusted Cindy's expertise with their personal homes and continue to recommend her to fellow co-workers and extended family. No doubt, Cindy has the work ethic and drive to put her clients first when marketing their home or seaching for a home that checks all the boxes! Experience counts with the largest investment most people make in a lifetime. Cindy Cawley's vast knowledge ensures your best interests are represented when selling or buying a home. Call Cindy today for your real estate needs in Omaha!

name: Christie Oberto
description: “There’s no place more important than home.” Christie Oberto believes this so strongly that she’s built her entire life around it. Although she’s traveled the world, she’s chosen to raise her family in the same Regency neighborhood where she grew up. And, whether it’s buying or selling, she goes above and beyond to help other families achieve their home goals as well. Christie elevates every stage of the real estate process with her warm, responsive professionalism and comprehensive, first-hand knowledge of the Omaha home market. Because Christie’s clients are often her neighbors—or referred to by her neighbors—she’s truly able to keep her finger on the pulse of what’s happening in the local market, and be a valued resource at every stage of the real estate process: from buying to renovating to selling. She understands that every home decision is part of a big-picture strategy. She has a strong sense of responsibility in being entrusted to guide her clients with her expertise and first-hand knowledge of Omaha real estate. As an Omaha native, a strong supporter of and volunteer with local charitable organizations and a mother of two school-aged children, Christie is invested in Omaha for life. She loves being the go-to when her clients have questions about anything— from ways to add value to your home or who to call for repairs, to fun local places to meet up with friends. “I find joy in the relationships, not just the transaction. I would rather exceed a client’s expectations and establish long-term rapport and trust rather than close a sale that may not be right.”

name: Steve Frantz
description: Steve is recognized leader in the local and national business arena, with a three-decade plus focus in real estate, financial services and banking. Steve currently serves as a Merger and Acquisitions Specialist in the Commercial Division of Berkshire Hathaway HS | Ambassador Real Estate.  In this role, he assists businesses wishing to transition in facilitating a buyer, works to find the appropriate structure for the transaction and assists in the transfer of Real Estate involved.  He has been affiliated with Berkshire Hathaway HS | Ambassador Real Estate since August of 2020. He also served in a consulting role for BHHSAMB in 2016 and 2017. Prior to this, Steve served as the Managing Director for the Private Banking Division of Mutual of Omaha Bank.  He served in this role in Omaha and Scottsdale from March 2018 until the bank was acquired by CIT Bank in August 2020. Steve lived in Denver Colorado in 2017, on a consulting assignment for a former high profile Wall Street CEO, rationalizing an expansion plan into Denver from the New York City operation. From 2010 to 2016, he served as President and Chairman of Tributary Mutual Funds, and as President of Tributary Capital Management LLC.  Steve re-engineered a declining investment management platform used primarily by the trust department of a community bank into a nationally known boutique asset manager utilized by industry heavyweights JP Morgan, UBS, Wells Fargo, Envestnet, PNC, Charles Schwab and Fidelity. During this time, Steve also served as President of Tributary Capital Management LLC.  In his tenure as leader, he grew the assets in the Flagship Small Cap strategy from $60 million in 2010 to over $1 billion in 2016.  The growth was almost exclusively sourced through channels outside of the parent banking organization.  The strategy and the firm have received multiple industry awards and accolades over Steve’s tenure, including the US News and World Report, Mutual Fund Observer, the Wall Street Journal and Pensions and Investments. Tributary was also awarded the Envestnet Small Cap SMA Manager of the year in 2016. Steve also served as Chief Compliance Officer for Tributary, managed the P&L, had sales and marketing responsibilities, key account client responsibilities as well as quarterly client calls on key portfolio and market related issues. Prior to his tenure at Tributary, Steve served for over a decade as Chief Investment Officer for Tributary’s parent, First National Bank of Omaha. He took on this role at a time when the bank was experiencing significant asset redemptions.  Over the ensuing decade, Steve guided the organization through a period of mass transformation. Steve’s previous experience includes J. Stephan Co. a third-party institutional asset management marketing firm, representing Thomson Horstmann and Bryant in Saddle Brook New Jersey, and Lazard London International, London England. Steve also held roles with Waddell and Reed Asset Management, Shawnee Mission Kansas and Parametric Portfolio Associates, Seattle Washington.  He began his financial services career as an account executive with Smith Barney Harris Upham in 1984 where he was a member of the constellation club, awarded annually to the top 15 rookie brokers across the country.  He also served as the local specialist in evaluating all private placement and publicly traded real estate transactions. He is a 1983 graduate of the University of Nebraska at Omaha, graduating with a degree in Business Administration. Steve significant experience in business has enabled him to take on national and local leadership roles in both the nonprofit and academic worlds as well.  He currently serves as the Audit Committee Chair for the National Board of Trustees of the March of Dimes, as well as serving on their National Volunteer Leadership Counsel.  He served two terms as the Chairman of the Board for the Nebraska Chapter and was voted the Volunteer of the year twice.  Steve served on the Board of Directors for the American Heart Association in Nebraska, where he was voted Volunteer of the Year in 1992.  He was a member of the First Capital Partners Advisory Board, a mid-market mezzanine finance firm in Omaha, the Iowa West Foundation Investment Committee, and served on the Omaha Community Partnership Board as well.  Steve was a member of Vistage International from 2013 – 2016, an international CEO mentoring and educational organization. Steve also served as an adjunct professor in the Executive MBA program for his alma mater.  His students, funded by a $1 million grant from First National Bank, managed a fixed income portfolio as part of their curriculum through the 2007-2009 financial crisis.  Two years in a row, his classes competed in and won the prestigious Dayton University competition, earning first place for risk adjusted performance. Steve has made several appearances on CNBC and Bloomberg TV and been quoted multiple times by the Wall Street Journal and the Omaha World Herald.  Steve is a sought-after speaker, having given over 100 speeches on various investment and economic related issues over his three-decade career.

name: Salem Real Estate Group
description: Jeff and Shannon Salem are the founders/team leaders and multi-million dollar producing agents with Salem Real Estate Group at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate. The team brings over a combined 40 years of sales/management experience in a wide variety of industries. They are passionate about Omaha real estate, and bring a unique ability to make the home-buying/selling experience as positive and fun as possible!

name: Chelsea Karlgaard
description: LUXURY HOME SPECIALIST | SKILLED DIGITAL MARKETING LISTING AGENT Times have changed in real estate and it's time to bring back the art of the deal while leveraging the latest technologies. My clients can expect that I deliver value in my data based market knowledge, organized systems that are designed to create a pleasant experience when buying or selling a property, and sharp negotiating skills that were honed by years of commodity purchasing. I work as both a listing agent and buyers agent, specializing in listings of luxury properties in the Omaha area. My clients include; first time buyers, new construction builds, luxury buyers & sellers and savvy real-estate investors looking for commercial or rental properties. I work diligently for my clients to fulfill their vision of prosperity. I look forward to working together, Chelsea Karlgaard MISSION: To be the preferred real estate professional with a tenacious focus on my clients while serving them with integrity, providing well informed real estate guidance while relentlessly pursuing a desire to consistently learn and evolve, to deliver my clients the most favorable real estate experience that enriches their lives. VALUES: 1. Serve clients best interest. 2. Persue exellence across all facets of conducting business. 3. Do the greatest amount of good for the greatest number of people I come in contact with through my life.

name: Cindy Kinzey
description: In today’s challenging markets you need a pro to help you find the keys to your dream home. I have the expertise to guide you through this market. I pride myself on always being available to offer you personal, one-on-one help with what some say is one of the biggest decisions you will make in your life. Your total satisfaction is my number one priority. I have built a reputation on client satisfaction, and I am devoted to making your move as easy and stress free as possible. Finding the right home is only the beginning. I will be there to assist you every step of the way. ABR  Accredited Buyer’s Representative: Specialized training representing Buyers ASP  Accredited Staging Professional: Expert knowledge on Staging homes CDPE  Certified Distressed Property Expert: Indepth knowledge of short sales and foreclosures CRS  Certified Residential Specialist: Proven experience, training and commitment to real estate MRP  Military Relocation Professional: Specialized training representing current and former military service members SRES  Senior Real Estate Specialist: Intensive training to better meet the needs of Seniors Licensed in Iowa and Nebraska! Consistently Ranks in Top 5% Nationally! National and International Referrals! Full-time REALTOR® since 2002! Graduate of The University of Iowa! Mother of 2 and a Golden Retriever!

name: Brodie Wakefield
description: Meet Brodie Providing help to others is Brodie’s top priority and has been for many years. Born and raised in Kennard, NE; Brodie found his passion for helping others by joining the Volunteer Fire Department. He is a graduate of the University of Nebraska at Omaha with a Bachelor’s degree in Emergency Management minoring in Business. Pursuing Real Estate has allowed him to use his expertise in management, communication, and familiarity with Omaha and the surrounding areas. Brodie will always go the extra mile to ensure his clients have a positive experience while buying, selling, or building a new home. He’s very passionate with what he does and wants nothing but success for his buyers and sellers!

name: Catherine Cizek Klavins
description: Welcome! I look forward to meeting you!

name: Deshazo Team Real Estate
description: We are the Deshazo Team, a husband and wife team of two dedicated realtors at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices.  We are devoted to helping both buyers and sellers in making their transactions go as smoothly as possible.  We are passionate in our field and making sure you find the right home to fit your needs or get the best value for your sale.  We can ensure you an open line of communication throughout the entire process and we are here to answer any questions along the way.  We can provide you with the latest market trends and activity and provide daily home searches. We live with our two daughters Alyssa and Aubrey in Papillion, Nebraska and serve all surrounding areas.  We believe that family is important and strive to work around your schedules and find the perfect home to fit your family's needs, just as we would want for ours.  We hope to help you in your next move!

name: Mahlon Rador
description: Meet Mahlon Meet Mahlon Rador!  Hard work and dedication are in his DNA. From working on the farm to serving as a Haz-mat technician and being a family man, he prides himself on great communication, guidance, and integrity.  Born and raised in the Cornhusker state, he has experienced city and rural living, enjoying all the recreation this great state has to offer.  Mahlon has earned real-life experience in customer service, sales, marketing, and real estate investing.  With a genuine love for real estate, he is thrilled to represent buyers and sellers in achieving homeownership.

name: Matt Pierce
description: As a Realtor, my first priority is to make my clients happy. I listen to clients' wants and needs to achieve the best outcome in every transaction, and I strive to ensure that the buying or selling process is fun, easy, and stress-free. My clients can count on me any time of day when they have a question or a concern. Teamed up with a great Lender, we like to create a team environment and hopefully take care of all the things that may be stressful for you resulting in a much better experience for you, the seller or buyer. Afterall, my success depends solely on the friendships we make as we go through this journey together. Trust and respect are my main concerns. I look forward to working with you and creating memories that will last a lifetime!

name: Pete Jenkins
description: Thanks for visiting my webpage! Born and raised in Omaha, I'm your full time real estate consultant and resource since 2000. When you need to make a move, call on a professional. With over $100M in lifetime sales and over 550 transactions, I can help you achieve the results you need and deserve. I look forward to working with you!

name: Andi Hallgren
description: Whether working with a luxury home owner, a seasoned investor or a first time home buyer, Andi prides herself on her unparalleled service and negotiation skills. She has a passion for working with both buyers and sellers, and strives to exceed in expectations with each and every client. Her extensive Creative and Marketing Director experience fosters innovation in marketing when selling your home. She holds a Bachelor of Arts from the University of Minnesota where she studied Psychology and Marketing. She has been in real estate since she was 6, and moved around a lot when she was younger. Growing up, she spent time visiting open houses and saw new and custom construction come to life. When she isn’t selling real estate, you can find her spending time with family and friends, training for her next triathlon, working on her lifestyle blog, and volunteering for community organizations such as Completely Kids, TeamMates Mentoring Program and Habitat for Humanity Friends Board.

name: Cindy Forehead
description: Meet Cindy Cindy has over 40 years’ experience in the greater Omaha metro area. Her approach with buyers and seller in every phase and her expertise in relocations to the area makes her a valuable resource. Cindy is consistently one of the areas highest producing agents, ranked in the top 1% nationally and in the Omaha market. Whether you are new to Omaha and looking for a home or are already established and ready to buy or sell, your first call should be to Cindy. Over half of Cindy’s clients are referrals from other satisfied clients, happy to recommend her to family, friends and business associates. In addition to her extensive experience, Cindy is well-connected in the community and provides a calm, knowledge-based approach to every client’s needs whether buying, selling or just considering options.

name: Jill Marie Bartling
description: Starting in the Real Estate business in 2002, I have the confidence, knowledge and expertise to help you with any of your Residential Real Estate needs.  I love helping every client find a home that perfectly fits their needs, whether it's buying an existing home or building a brand new one.  Born and raised in South Omaha, Nebraska,  As a child, we always took Sunday drives and my Dad drove us home "the long way", so little did I know I was learning how to take every back road and alley in town.  By the time I was 16, I was driving Omaha knowing exactly where I was going and how to take a detour to get there faster if I needed to. What I love about Omaha, is we are your Little Big Town.  Omaha, Nebraska maintains that “small town” feeling, with some big city amenities. Enjoy the World Famous, Omaha Henry Doorly Zoo, catch a College World Series Baseball game at Charles Schwab Field in June, People watch in the Old Market while attending the Summer Arts Festival and Farmers Markets, visit the newest & best family friendly downtown, the Gene Leahy Mall & River Waterfront parks.   Don't forget to entice your appetite with some of the best eats around, like the Reuben Sandwich created right here in Omaha.  Walk the 3000 sq. ft. floating bridge over the Missouri River from downtown Omaha to Council Bluffs, Iowa.  (yes, it's walkable, you can place one foot in Nebraska & one foot in Iowa at the same time!). My main goal for every client, let me handle the complex details, so it's an easy transition from home to home for you. If you're selling, buying, investing or building, I'm happy to help! My Credentials Licensed in 2002 2006 Graduate of the Realtor Institute (GRI) Member of the National Association of Realtors Member of the Omaha Area Board of Realtors Multiple Recipient of the Million Dollar Circle Award – 2003, 2004, 2005, 2006, 2007, 2010-2022 Multiple Recipient of Monthly Top Listing Agent, Top Closing Agent & Top Sales Agent & Outstanding Performer awards – 2012-2022 Multiple Recipient for Yearly All Company Top Listing New Construction Agent – 2012-2022 2017 - All Company Top New Construction in Units Sold 2018 - Ranked #11 in the State of Nebraska for Individuals Sales 2018 - Highest Productivity by an Individual Agent 2018- Summit & Platinum Circle Award Winner 2019 & 2020 - President's Circle Award Winner 2021 – Leading Edge Award Winner 2022 - Gold Circle Award Winner 2022 – TOP 10 (#9) – 4th Qtr, out of 46,000 Realtors Nationwide in the Homeservices NATIONAL network 2022 – TOP 25 –(#24) – 4th Quarter in Berkshire Hathaway NATIONAL Network for Units sold 2022 – TOP 5 (#3)- 4th Quarter in Berkshire Hathaway STATE Network for Units sold 2014, 2015, 2017, 2018, 2019, 2020 & 2022 - Voted BEST OF SARPY COUNTY REALTOR - People's Choice Award

name: Kylie Davis
description: I was born and raised in Nebraska, attended a small-town public school, and made the move to Omaha in 2011. I studied Business Administration & Real Estate at the University of Nebraska at Omaha. I am passionate, confident, determined and open-minded, I am a hard-worker and get the job done. I’ve been in the business since 2016 and have a passion for sales and marketing.

name: Julie Dunbar
description: Lake living offers the romantic promise of always being on vacation, enjoying the water, a boat, a beach and a comfortable place to gather with family and friends. A lake home owner herself, Julie knows how important it is for buyers and sellers to have access to comprehensive information and market data regarding all of the various lake communities. This website is designed to be your one-stop shop for the luxury lake properties just west of Omaha in Waterloo and Valley. Browse all of the available lake properties, and the historical sold data, and imagine yourself in the waterfront home that you have always dreamed about. Consider whether you want an agent who understands lake property and who is able to provide the buyer side with a clear picture of what life is going to be like in each of the lake communities. Julie has created this website with you in mind. From the highest quality property images, helpful sold data and other useful information, Julie is here to make your lake home buying or selling experience smooth and stress-free. Find out more about Luxury Lake Living at www.JulieDunbar.com

name: Tabitha Cooper
description: MEET TABITHA Thank you for visiting my page! I am thrilled to help you find your new home or help you sell your existing home. Real Estate is a genuine passion of mine and being a Veteran of the United States Air Force and married to a Retired USAF stud muffin, we know a thing or two about BUYING AND SELLING homes :) Having been the trainer here at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate, I am immensely qualified to walk through this process with you, hand in hand, answering any and all questions along the way and having fun while doing it. Buying and Selling homes can be super stressful. But, it can also be super exciting. The thrill of buying a brand new home, your first ever home, downsizing, upsizing, buying an investment property etc...this process should me memorable (in a good way). The thrill of selling a home so that you can move on to the next phase or chapter in your life, turning that equity into (cash monies), should also be a memorable process (in a good way). If you are in the market to buy, sell, invest or even CHAT about possibilities, please call or text me. I promise you will not be disappointed in my services. Click here to Review my Testimonials. My husband and I also represent Horizon Homes so if you're in it to win it with a brand new custom built home, click here to check out our Models. For immediate questions, call Aaron Cooper at 402-709-1117 Call or text me today at 402-210-5055

name: Ashley Sum
description: Ashley Sum, born and raised in Omaha, joined the Lori Paul Team in 2012.  She has worked at BHHS Ambassador as the Brokers Assistant for 6 years prior to getting licensed.  She has the resources and background knowledge to provide her clients with exceptional service. Ashley studied at the University of Nebraska-Omaha and graduated in 2010 with a Bachelors of Science in Marketing and Management.  After college she attended Randall School of Real Estate and continues to attend classes to educate herself with new trends and business idea to better her customer service. Ashley completed the Brian Buffini Peak Producers course and focuses on creating and maintaining relationships with her clients. When Ashley is not servicing her clients, she is active in her Neighborhood Homeowners Association/Board and serve on various committees at her church. She also enjoys staying active by running and spending time with family and friends.

name: Chapin Sellin-Kurtz
description: MEET CHAPIN Welcome and thanks for finding me here! I am a lifelong Omaha resident. I grew up in midtown and I have always loved old homes and tree lined streets.I have watched Omaha grown over the decades and my comprehensive knowledge of the city can be put to work for you. After graduating from Creighton University in 2006 with a BSBA in Marketing my real estate career started in property management. I worked for a national real estate investment trust (REIT). I enjoyed working in the real estate industry and received my sales licence in 2010. I learned quickly that just like every home, every real estate transaction is different. I understand that this industry requires staying current in market trends, good communication and above all else honesty. I pride myself on protecting my clients interests with integrity and honesty. Real estate is not my only passion. Since receiving my license I married my best friend and we now have two daughters. Our four legged-fur kid is a Golden Retriever, Pearl. When I am not selling real estate or attending kid activites, my husband and I love to travel. I also enjoy spending time with my family, entertaining friends and being active. What can you expect when working with me? My clients work directly with me and we walk through the process of buying and/or selling a home together. The real estate market can be challenging but with proactive problem solving we can navigate it together. In my opinion, communication is key and is the foundation to success. A home is the biggest investment most of us will ever make. I hope that when it is time for you to make your dream come true you will allow me to help you see it through.

name: Kelly Kontz
description: Known for delivering personalized attention, out-of-the-box thinking and referral-worthy experiences, Kelly Kontz thrives in the luxury home market with her “client first” mentality. Her real estate business has grown to be one of the top in Omaha, just through the word of mouth from her clients! Very impressive! She is a true businesswoman who just happens to sell real estate… “To me, success in real estate is all about the relationships I have with my clients... I consider my clients my friends & I feel truly blessed that I can be a small part of such a big decision in their lives. What a wonderful & rewarding experience handing them their Keys! I love to see them smile! Kelly has been setting and achieving big goals ever since graduating from Minnesota State University in Mankato with a double major in marketing & management in a record 3 1⁄2 years! Kelly is an accomplished entrepreneur who is not afraid of taking risks. Before getting into real estate over 14 years ago, Kelly started a very successful event planning business in Sioux Falls, SD, a performance dog biscuit business in Billings, MT and now along with being a Multi-Million Dollar Club Producing Realtor, Kelly owns The Key Group – A Premier Real Estate Group; Staged & Rearranged, P.C., a professional home staging company; Pride in Properties, a rental management company. Her most rewarding collaboration, though, is her family – Husband of 20 years Steve and two sons, Nick and Alex.

name: Allen Osborn
description: Meet Allen Osborn! Allen was born and raised in western Nebraska, attended the University of Nebraska Kearney, and currently resides in Omaha. For the last decade, he has developed and prospered relationships through his teaching and coaching career. Allen has a passion for public service and strives to build strong relationships and connections through a person-served lens, which aligns with his real estate endeavors. With a background in sales and management, he prides himself on effective communication and having a strong work ethic. He acts with integrity to treat each person as family through their buying, selling, and investment goals.

name: Marie Otis
description: Home It's more than four walls and a roof over your head.  It's a place where families come together to create memories that will last for generations. Whether I am representing you in the sale of your current home or assisting you in finding your new home, it is an honor to be a part of creating your family memories. In the 16 years I have been a Realtor I have worked with many different types of clients from military families, to first time buyers, to relocating families, to downsizing empty-nesters. The common traits I believe all clients are looking for is someone who will listen, take the time to understand their wants and needs in their next home and educate them on the process of buying, selling or building a home. I will do everything in my power to deliver the results you expect with state of the art communication, a detailed and organized plan of action, marketing, web presence and Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate technology. Let me put my expertise to work for you today and let's get started on those memories!

name: Karen Jennings
description: STANDING TALL FOR YOU! As a passionate and persistent Realtor, I'm humbled and honored to provide quality leadership with the highest degree of integrity. Developing a solid, trustworthy relationship with my clients is the key. My experience includes Corporate and Military Relocation, Single Family Homes including Luxury Homes, New Construction, Acreages, Farms, and Commercial properties. I have been helping clients buy and sell real estate since 2002 and am licensed in both Nebraska and Iowa. I am a member of the National Association of Realtors, Omaha Area Board of Realtors, Great Plains Multiple Listing Service, Midlands Regional Commercial Information Exchange, and Nebraska Real Estate Association. As the leader of the JENNINGS TEAM, I look forward to serving you! Luxury Collection Specialist Voted Best of Omaha Winner 2024, 2023, 2022, 2021, 2020, 2019, 2018, 2017, 2016, 2015, 2014, 2013 Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate: Chairman’s Circle Award:  2023, 2022, 2021, 2020, 2019, 2018 Top 5 for Pinnacle Award - Medium Teams 2023 Top 5 for Oracle Award - Medium Teams 2023 Top 5 for Shooting Star Award 2023 Summit Award for 2nd Highest Agent Productivity 2023 5 Year Legend Award 2022 Nominated for Pinnacle & Oracle Awards 2022 Top 25 Nationally GCI Volume Mid Size Team 2021 Diamond Award Winner Medium Teams 2021 Nominated for Pinnacle, Oracle, Big Deal Award 2021 Oracle Award for Large Team Producer 2020 Pinnacle Award for Top Large Team Number of Transactions 2020 Summit Award for Team Productivity (#7) 2020 Shooting Star Awards for Number of Transactions & Production (Mid Size/Large/Mega) 2020 #3 Top Commercial Sales Volume 2020 TOP TEN NATIONALLY Number of Units Sold Mid Size Team 2020 Oracle Award for Large Team Producer 2018 Pinnacle Award for Number of Transactions, Top Large Team 2018 Summit Award for Team Productivity 2018 Shooting Star Awards for Number of Transactions & Production 2018 CBSHOME Real Estate: All Company Top Producer Team 2018, 2017, 2016, 2015, 2014, 2013 All Company Top Producer Individual 2012, 2011, 2010, 2009 Other: Nebraska Realtors Association Leadership Academy 2024 50 Over 50 Award Winner for Nebraska 2023 UNL Young Alumni Achievement Award - 2010 All-Time Leading Basketball Scorer (Male or Female) for University of Nebraska Inducted into the NCAA Academic All-American Hall of Fame - 2008 Retired Jersey 51 - University of Nebraska Inducted into Inaugural Class of University of Nebraska Athletics Hall of Fame - 2015 Played Professional Basketball in France & Member of 1992 USA National Team University of Nebraska - Hall of Fame Board Member Motivational Speaker Education: Randall School of Real Estate – 2001 Master's Degree in Physical Therapy (UNMC) - 1998 Bachelor's Degree in Exercise Science (UNL) - 1993 Jennings Team Members: Karen Jennings Missy Turner Don OBryan Sam Baratta

name: Nicole Mattson
description: Nicole brings time-tested business acumen and a genuine desire to help to all clients. Nicole is driven and knows hard work gets results. Without any encouragement from family, Nicole made the decision to seek higher education and was awarded a full ride academic scholarship to Creighton University, thereby becoming the first person in her family to graduate from college. Upon graduation she enjoyed a career in sales for companies like Xerox and Pfizer. She’ll put her many years as a sales professional to work for you.  She will focus on your needs and treat you like a valued friend throughout the buying and selling process. Nicole is happy to help you with all of your real estate needs.

name: Rachel Skradski Luhrs
description: Meet Rachel Rachel is a successful agent with a devotion to high principals. She is truly sage beyond her years. Dedicated, forward thinking, and a disciplined leader with over 12 years of real estate coaching, she has an understanding of goal setting, and is dedicated to her work at the highest level. Rachel is enthusiastic, outgoing, and personable. Her positive mindset will win you over. Rachel appreciates the special support needed for first-time home buyers or sellers and understands how to service the most experienced homeowners. Her professional awards and achievements are impressive but even more impressive is her approach to service and area knowledge, helping ensure her clients make the right choice for the needs.

name: Bill Simmons
description: Bill Simmons is a Real Estate professional with Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate licensed in Nebraska and Iowa. Proudly serving the Greater Omaha Area. Standing beside you every step of the way. From the Loess Hills of Iowa to the Platte River of Nebraska, I'm dedicated in helping you find the home of your dreams. As your devoted, full time REALTOR®, my market knowledge and experience provides you information you need to make the best real estate decision. I will deliver a professional, honest service as I assist you in buying or selling Real Estate. Whether it be finding properties that fit you and your family's requirements, financial planning, negotiating deals and executing closings. Preparing a comparative market analysis, analyzing the best way to market your home or giving you tips on preparing your home for sale. If you are ready to get into investment properties I have firsthand knowledge as owner of BGE Properties, LLC, with an A+ accredited rating with the Better Business Bureau. Owning single family and multiple unit properties as well as many rehabs. I also hold the designation of Residential Investment Specialist (RIS).

name: Lynn Smith
description: After several years of reviewing new home floor plans from my kitchen table that my husband brought home, I made the decision to embark on a career in real estate. For the past seven years, I have taken great pride in serving as a dedicated representative for Pine Crest Villas, specializing in new construction. My passion lies in guiding individuals and families through the intricate journey of home building, irrespective of their prior experience in the process. My utmost satisfaction derives from facilitating the realization of people's dream homes while ensuring that the entire experience remains as seamless and enjoyable as possible.  I have 3 grown children and a caring husband, all of whom support me in all my endeavors. In my spare time I love to bake by trying new recipes that my family often ask if they can have some or are you taking this to someone else?

name: Kim Hoffart
description: Kim has been selling residential real estate for over 30 years. She was born and raised in Omaha, and graduated from Westside High School and The University of Nebraska - Lincoln with a major in Communications. Kim has been blessed over the years with many repeat clients and referrals. Finding just the right home for her clients is a top priority. She believes there is no better satisfaction than seeing a family's house become a home to them. Kim stays very involved in your own neighborhood chairing the activities committee and being a member of the HOA board. In her free time, she enjoys spending time with friends and family.

name: Sheila Ost
description: Pursuing My Dream as a Real Estate Agent As a real estate agent, I am living my dream career. I am a reliable, determined, and passionate professional who thrives on the excitement of helping my clients realize their home ownership goals. I am excited at the prospect of working with you! Though I earned my degree in Elementary Education, I took a different path. I spent two decades working for Fortune 500 companies before becoming involved in my husband's construction business. I am a mother to three amazing children who have taught me the value of scheduling, whether it's school, sports or extracurricular activities. As part of Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate, I know the importance of working with an agent who has your best interests at heart. Providing exceptional customer service is my top priority, along with unwavering commitment and loyalty to each client. Supported by a company that understands the ever-changing real estate landscape, I am able to offer a comprehensive range of services, including relocation, financing, title insurance, and much more.

name: Terry Cooper
description: I have been in sales since 1977--office supplies (mostly clerking!), cleaning products, hardware, electronics and appliances--until returning to Iowa Western to receive my Associates Degree in Communications in 1987. Two years with New York Life as a Registered Representative prepared me for a long stint in the auto industry, 1991 to 2002, and a return stretch 2007 to 2017. And now...Real Estate!

name: Kristie Kuo
description: Kristie Kuo is a real estate agent for Nebraska and Iowa areas and is affiliated with Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate. Prior to formalizing her expertise as a Realtor, she has purchased and sold multiple properties over the two decades she and her family has resided in the Midwest. Drawing from her own personal experience as a seller, a buyer, an investor, a private lender and even as a real estate client, Kristie believes that an exceptional real estate experience entails treating her clients as if she were representing her own family member. Consequently, you can trust that she will represent your best interests and boldly negotiate on your behalf. Fluent in Mandarin (Chinese), Taiwanese, and Spanish. Kriste Kuo | Realtor Serving your Nebraska & Iowa real estate needs! What Kristie loves: Love Photography Love Playing Piano & Cello Love Dogs Love Baking Love Gardening Love Coffee & Tea Love Trying Different Ethnic Food Love Travel

name: Melissa Cartwright
description: I began my career in Real Estate in 2018. I enjoy creating long lasting relationships with my clients and being their trusted Realtor®. Buying or selling a home can be stressful. I pride myself on creating as smooth of a transaction as possible and more importantly, providing my clients with a greater experience.  I specialize in assisiting homebuyers and sellers in the greater Omaha area. Wheather you are a first time homebuyer or seasoned investor I will work tirelessly to promote your best interest always. I will work with you to get the fairest price, in the least amount of time, and provide you with the best market data to inform and assist you in the negotiation process.  When I'm not busy helping my clients, you can find me at the gym, spending time with my husband and son, or trying out a new recipe in the kitchen. It would be a pleasure and honor to work with you.

name: Shawn Hovey
description: Shawn is the owner of Foundry Home Realty Group, LLC and a co-owner and principal designer at Foundry Home Interior Design, Inc.  Shawn has a Master of Science in Architecture with a Specialization in Interior Design from the University of Nebraska – Lincoln as well as undergraduate degrees in Art History and Interior Design. Staying ahead of the curve as an innovator, change maker, top producer & trend setter, Shawn is committed to bringing fresh ideas to the marketplace.  Her passion, talent & expertise has gained her numerous accolades in the industry acquired in over 20 years of experience in the business.  She is an expert in all aspects of real estate and design from ideation to valuation. “Real Estate, new construction, remodeling & interior design are challenging and equally fulfilling lines of work.  Being a professional real estate agent and interior designer is both fascinating & rewarding.  It is such an honor to be able to use my knowledge, skill & talent to positively impact peoples’ lives and add value.” Shawn’s interests include global interior dynamics, evidence-based design, the history of interior furnishings, material culture & the demonstrated positive economic impact interior design has on new construction real estate values. Remaining active in the community with civic and charity events is important to Shawn.  Her design was featured in the KETV Channel 7 Showcase Home (proceeds from the tickets sales for this home tour went to Angels Among Us).  Shawn also supports the Sunshine Kids Charity & the Ronald McDonald House.  Her time outside of work is spent with her family & friends, visiting art galleries, listening to live music & traveling.

name: Leah Johnson
description: Meet Leah! Hi! I'm Leah, a Council Bluffs native and licensed real estate agent in Iowa and Nebraska. I'm the Team Leader of Fairway Real Estate Group, a small real estate team at BHHS Ambassador Real Estate. My niches include helping first-time buyers navigate the home buying process and working with sellers to get top dollar for their homes. I'm also an investor-friendly agent! My mission in real estate is to do things the "Fair Way" and to make the home buying and selling process as smooth and easy for you as possible. I also like thinking outside of the box when it comes to lending options for buyers and finding creative ways to market the home for sellers. If you meet me, you'll see I'm bubbly, outgoing, and genuine. My clients appreciate my transparency and I like to "keep it real". I pride myself on being responsive and available for my clients, whether it's evenings, weekends, or holidays. When I'm not watching my kids play sports, I enjoy traveling, playing golf, or trying out a new restaurant. Whether you're a buyer, seller, or investor, I'd love to work with you!

name: Fred Tichauer
description: In the Omaha metro area, Fred Tichauer is highly regarded for his unparalleled knowledge of residential real estate investment. In addition to being a long-time investor, he is an Associate Broker with Berkshire Hathaway Ambassador Real Estate. Fred teaches continuing education classed approved by the Nebraska Real Estate Commission. To date, more than 1100 Realtors in the Omaha metro area have enrolled in his courses, as well as hundreds more throughout the country. He takes a great deal of pride in the fact that many of his clients and former students are now millionaire real estate investors. With half a century of success as an investor, Fred understands the ins and outs of the investment niche market form the perspectives of the investor and agent. His proven system will push you to achieve your financial objectives. Fred holds himself to a high moral standard and would never encourage a client to purchase a property that he would not consider purchasing himself. Rather than focusing on his next commission check , Fred devotes his energy to helping his clients accomplish their financial goals. When you succeed, he succeeds. Throughout his long career, Fred has earned a reputation for being honest, straightforward, and providing only sound strategies that have worked for him. As his client or student, you can expect excellence, trust, commitment, integrity, leadership, practical knowledge, expertise, and results. As an a entrepreneur, Fred controls a sizable real estate portfolio generating a six-figure income. He has flipped more than 150 properties and coached clients to flip over 500. He believes there's nothing better than a real estate investment portfolio consisting of residential properties located in "family-friendly" neighborhoods. He is certain that anyone who is creditworthy and is willing to work hard can achieve the financial freedom they deserve.

name: Emily Garden
description: I have a passion for helping clients find their dream home in a seamless and stress-free manner. Whether you are a first-time homebuyer or looking to upgrade to your forever home, I am committed to providing exceptional service and personalized attention to help you achieve your real estate goals. Let's work together to make your real estate dreams a reality!

name: William Barker
description: As your Realtor, I will guide you through every step of the home selling process. You will never feel pressured, rushed or like you're "just another number." My goal is to provide value and make your experience seamless, enjoyable and stress free. I have extensive knowledge of the Nebraska housing market and will aggressively negotiate on behalf of my clients. My experience ranges from first-time home buyers to luxury properties. From personal homes to investment properties, land, and commercial buildings, I will sell them quickly and for maximum profit.

name: Gail Hunter
description: Gail Hunter is the father of Blake, Brian and Rachel Hunter. He began his real estate career in 1980. Gail is a past president and board member of the Union Pacific Railroad Museum and Priesthood Member of the Community of Christ Church. He is a third-generation auctioneer and has been involved in hundreds of successful real estate and benefit auctions. He is a graduate of the Certified Auctioneer’s Institute and the Missouri School of Auction. Contact Gail at 402-677-5441 or Gail.Hunter@bhhsamb.com.

name: Aaron Cooper
description: I'm a realtor who's passionate about family, fishing and Real Estate. I retired from the USAF w/ over 21 yrs of service and am looking forward to continue serving others. We're at 12509 Quail Drive, Bellevue if you'd like to BUILD, BUY or SELL. My wife and I are teamed up and ready to go to work for you! Come see me in the Liberty Model at 12509 Quail Dr, Bellevue NE 68123

name: Jeff Johnson
description: Hi, I'm Jeff Johnson with Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices | Ambassador Real Estate.  As a commercial real estate specialist, I represent clients in the sale and leasing of all types of commercial properties including office, retail, industrial and multi-family among other uses. I've worked in commercial real estate for over 20 years with a background in finance and development prior to brokerage.  What I enjoy most about brokerage is using my expertise for the benefit of my clients and being a resource to them when making real estate decisions for their business or as an investment.  In today's competitive marketplace, it helps to have an experienced agent who understands your business objectives and presents opportunities that you wouldn't necessarily discover on your own. If you'd like help with a property in Nebraska or Iowa, contact me today to get started.

name: Heidi Steskal
description: There are so many agents to choose from in this industry.  What qualities are you looking for in a realtor?  Someone who is genuine and trustworthy?  Someone that will be honest with you and who cares and listens to your needs and wants? Characteristics like these are important when dealing with possibly your biggest asset.  Whether you are purchasing, selling or investing in real estate, I'm driven to provide you with an experience that exceeds the norm.  My ambition is to gain you as a friend and client for life. Professional real estate agent for the Omaha and Lincoln area.

name: Shelli Novotny
description: MEET SHELLI I am a full time Realtor. I have an Associate Brokers License. I have been selling real estate since Aug. of 2003. I work the Omaha Metro and Surrounding Area.I am one of  the area's top producing Residential Realtors. I pride myself in helping all my clients meet their real estate goals. Let me help you get what you deserve! I have strong negotiating skills, I am driven to get the job done, I pay attention to detail, I never give up, and I have great realtionships with people in the real estate industry. I work off good rumors. My Clients number one goal is My number one Goal. Take my 18 years of experience and allow it to go to work for you. I have been blessed with many opportunities to serve many people. It would be a pleasure to get to know you and help you reach your real estate goals. The best way to reach me is through my private cell phone is 402-250-7042 I am a Veterans United Realty Endorsed Agent I am a Rocket Mortgage Endorsed Agent I work with Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Relocation Dept. which is one of the largest in the Network. Shelli Novotny Associate Broker/ Team Leader Real Estate 1 Team realestate1group.com

name: Lyn Echter
description: Integrity. Service. Knowledge is what I feel are the most important attributes to being a successful real estate agent. I am a MULTI-MILLION TOP PRODUCER and have been selling real estate in Omaha and the surrounding area for many years.  Many years ago, I decided to become a Certified Home Stager. I thought having this certification would be a HUGE benefit to my sellers….and it truly has.  I have been STAGING all the homes I list for the past ten years…. and it works.  There is no cost for this service.  I have a warehouse full of furniture, accessories, pillows, artwork plus more! Having come from a background of years of Customer Service, I am able to bring top notch services to sellers and buyers with professionalism, honesty, and integrity. I am interested in helping you find or sell your “home”—not just buy or sell a “house”. Buying or selling a home can cause much stress and excitement at the same time.  I understand; and as your Realtor, I’m with you every step of the way. You will know what to expect during the entire transaction as I am always available and have clear and honest communication throughout the process. I will ALWAYS have YOUR best interests. To me, success in the profession I work in, is all about the relationships I have with my clients. My job is to listen to my buyers and sellers needs and wants and to go above and beyond their expectations. From First time home buyers to empty nesters ~~ I am so VERY GRATEFUL & BLESSED to be a part of any phase in buyers or sellers lives ~ Please follow my Facebook page at: www.facebook.com/LynEchterAndTeam . There you will see informational posts about the real estate market plus many testimonials from many past buyers and sellers! If you want more information as to what my services entail along with great tips for buyers and sellers, please visit my website at www.echterhomes.com .

name: Heather Peterson
description: Born and raised in the cornhusker state I have the knowledge of the Omaha area.  I bought my first house as new construction at the young age of 21. I owned my own rental in the Aksarben area. I am looking to be your guide to the home that you create lifetime memories in as your forever agent.

name: Jeff Nogg
description: Raised in Omaha, NE, I left home to go to college at University of Wisconsin-Madison before settling in Atlanta, GA, after college, with an opportunity in the healthcare recruiting industry.  In 2005, I decided to move back to Omaha, NE to raise my family & co-own our long-time family moving and storage company, I-Go Van & Storage.  We are one of the top United Van Lines agents around the country and relocate people from any origin location to any destination location…. locally, across the country, and around the world!!. Between recruiting and relocation, my background is rooted in client life transition, and deciding to additionally take my skills into the real estate industry fits very well with that!  My goal is to reduce your stress, as much as possible, in your real estate transaction!! I'm a Realtor® with BHHS Ambassador Real Estate, The Bjork Group, in Omaha, NE and the surrounding areas. I’m excited to meet you!  I pledge to provide you with the excellent customer service you deserve!  My focus is on the long-term relationship with my clients & I want to be your “realtor for life”!  Just give me the opportunity!

name: Carmen Bunde
description: Full-Time REALTOR ® helping you move on or move in to your next home!  #callcarmenfirst Your Trusted Expert I guide you through the technical and sometimes emotional process of buying, selling, building, or investing in real estate. I listen to YOUR goals to create a positive experience through a variety of concierge services, reducing your stress wherever I can, and focusing on what matters most to you. These efforts have resulted in consistently earning repeat clients and referrals. I am dedicated and passionate about serving my clients with care and expertise through all stages of life: first-time home buyers, upsizing, downsizing, divorce, expanding family, relocating into or out of town, power of attorney, and moving to independent living. Licensed in Nebraska, I also vet and refer to agents across the country. If you, or someone you know, is considering a move in the next couple years, let's work together! Forever Agent "Carmen has been fantastic! She helped us find a new home, sell our old home, and is now helping us sell my mom's house. She is very knowledgeable and thorough with everything she does. She is honest and sincere and truly cares about helping. I felt like she really took the time and had a great ability to understand us and our needs and wants. We are very happy in our new home and appreciate how she made the process enjoyable for us." Julie F. REALTOR ® vs Real Estate Agent? Only a REALTOR ® is a member of the National Assocation of REALTORS ® and abides by its strict Code of Ethics.  As a REALTOR ® , I focus on constant learning and professional development in a changing environment to serve clients with respect and to be knowledgeable of and apply the most up-to-date best practices. description: Gehrki Group The Gehrki Group has 30+ years in listing and selling Real Estate closing over 1,000 home sales with over $200 million in production. Joe has specialized in all forms of residential real estate sales. name: Townsend Lanphier Group
description: Get to Know Ann & Kathy Whether you're working directly with Ann or Kathy, you'll always have access to both. That's because, while they each have different experiences and skillsets, they work together and share a common goal of making sure their clients have the best buying and selling experiences possible. Every time. Making Moves Happen in the Community for More Than 25 Years Serving Omaha, Elkhorn, Bellevue, Bennington, Gretna, La Vista, Papillion, Ralston and more! Two is Better Than One What makes us different from other real estate agents? Other than the fact that we truly do go above and beyond in all aspects of our job? (And, no, we're not afraid to say that.) With us, you're basically getting two for one. While you have one point of contact, you also have access to both of us and our strengths. What are those exactly? Read below and we'll tell you all about our professional experience, our points of expertise, and even a few of our favorite things. Ann Townsend Ann.Townsend@bhhsamb.com 402.706.3037 Residential Investment Specialist MRP (Military Referral Program) As part of a relocated family, Ann has the first-hand experience with all the emotions, stress and logistics of moving a household, family and life to a new city. With a father who is a disabled veteran, transitioning military families in and out of our community is her sweet spot. Ann and her husband used to own a real estate portfolio of 48 units until she decided to go into residential real estate in 2011. Now, with a real estate background, relocation experience, an accounting degree and community involvement, Ann is able to sell Omaha, find the right house and ensure her clients get the best prices for the house they are buying or selling. Ann uses all the tools available to ensure her clients get into their dream homes. Known for her honesty, integrity and dedication, Kathy always has the best interest of her buyers and sellers at heart. Ann works with the Omaha Chamber of Commerce, Omaha Children’s Hospital, Creighton University HCOB, ABIDE, Catholic Charities, JDRF and Little White Dog Rescue "I am an agent you can trust to be at your side during the entire home-buying process. Exceeding expectations, responsive communication and personal customer service are hallmarks of my business. This high-level of service is what you can expect to receive as I use all tools available to ensure you end up in your dream home. Because you MATTER, I am always on your side." – Ann Townsend Kathy Lanphier kathy.lanphier@bhhsamb.com 402.670.1040 Corporate Relocation Specialist Kathy has been a licensed real estate agent for more than 20 years now. Many of those years were spent as a Domestic and International Corporate Relocation specialist. As a well-connected professional within the Omaha business community, she has her finger on the pulse of local corporations. Kathy is truly at her best when there are multiple balls in the air and she can alleviate stress for her client, helping them make clear decisions. With a father who was a farmer and mother who was a schoolteacher, she learned what grit, perseverance and hard work were at a very early age. Not many realtors take on the roles of organizer, stager, photographer, handyman, therapist, housekeeper, painter, tour guide, savvy marketer and keen negotiator, but Kathy does it all. Give her the challenge and she will bring you the result. "I consistently surprise people with an innate ability to make good things happen. I pay attention to every detail and will stand behind you every step of the way, developing a relationship of trust through knowledge, patience and good humor. I ensure that the process of negotiating the logistical, emotional and financial hurdles of your transaction will be made as easy as possible." – Kathy Lanphier

name: Denise Poppen
description: REALTOR® Nebraska - 25 Years Experience Full-time Listing and Buyers Agent Customer Service: My clients wants and needs are my number one goal!! : With a passion for real estate and a commitment to exceptional service, I am dedicated to helping my clients achieve their real estate goals. As a full-time licensed REALTOR®  with Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate with 25 years of experience in the Omaha and its surrounding areas market, I bring a wealth of knowledge and expertise to every transaction. Why Choose Me: I understand that buying or selling a home is one of the most important financial decisions you will make, and I am here to guide you through every step of the process. My priority is to ensure that my clients feel informed, supported, and confident throughout their real estate journey. Services I Offer: Buyer Representation: Whether you're a first-time homebuyer, you have owned before or you're an investor, I will work tirelessly to find the perfect property to meet your needs and budget. Seller Representation: Utilizing cutting-edge marketing strategies and industry connections, I will help you sell your home quickly and for the best possible price.
