name: Yaeline Ramos
description: Yaeline launched her career as a realtor with Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate. She currently resides in Red Oak, Iowa and services Nebraska and Iowa. Yaeline graduated from Red Oak High School and went on to pursue a degree in Psychology at the University of Nebraska at Omaha. Yaeline quickly realized that she was following the crowd and was not following her true life's purpose. After much thought, she gained the courage to leave college and follow her dreams; and worked towards a more fulfilling endeavor, obtaining her real estate license. Though taking a leap of faith can be frightening, she continues to remind herself, “What if it can turn out better than you can imagine?” Yaeline is best known for her optimism and her ability to problem solve. With a passion for helping people, she is dedicated to helping you and your family secure the house of your dreams or sell your home. As a client of hers, she will take the stress off your hands while also making sure you’re informed, involved, and satisfied.

name: Steve Scherich
description: "I don't horse around when it comes to real estate" Finding your dream home shouldn't be like looking for a needle in a haystack, it just takes an agent with integrity and patience. I’m celebrating twenty nine years of service, specializing in premier properties and acreages. I’m so appreciative and proud that most of my business is referred to me by the many clients I’ve served over the past 29 years.  I work hard to stay true to my saying, “I don’t horse around when it comes to real estate” and I’ll work hard for you too! Over the years my clients have referred me to their co-workers, friends, family and adult children and now their adult grandchildren. My goal is to have you refer me too! If you’re buying, selling, relocating, or building, let's connect! The pleasure is mine and thank you for your time, Steve

description: It’s no secret, there’s a lot of realtors in our metro area! I’ve had the privilege of working with many of them over the past 6 plus years. I hope to continue fostering those business relationships and build more connections with realtors and my clients. As a realtor, it’s our duty to protect our clients' interests throughout the entire transaction. What I bring to the table is constant real estate education including law and ethics, loyalty, organization, communication and marketing. I have extensive real estate photography experience and have worked with home stagers to perfect the first thing prospective buyers see- the photographs of your home. My family has been endlessly supportive of all local small businesses, including ours. My husband and son are flooring installers and are extremely handy around the house. My daughter is also a marketer and provides graphics, and my soon to be daughter-in law cleans homes. I love what I do and look forward to growing in real estate in the Omaha/Council Bluffs Metro Area!

I work with a team of trusted contacts to help serve you in every aspect of the moving process including staging, packing, home repairs, and estate sales. My goal as an agent with Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Real Estate is to offer this "onestop shopping" approach to simplify your real estate business transaction, as well as to make your move fun and easy. 2021 Voted Sarpy County "Favorite Realtor" 2021 Ranked #5 Top 1% of company- $23.2 Mil Sales 2015 | '16 | '17 | '18 | '21 Circle of Excellence (highest level of sales) 2020 Ranked #6 Top 1% of company 2019 Ranked #8 Top 1% of company 2018 Top Referral Award 2018 Ranked #9 Top 1% of company 2018 | 2021 Chairman's Circle Gold (over $14 million in sales) 2017 Top Producer Individual 2017 Ranked #8 Top 1% of company 2015 Top Referral - Sarpy office 2015 Top Outstanding Achievement - Sarpy office

description: Jace has a natural knack at helping his clients feel well cared for and understood. He takes great pride in helping them find the perfect home for their needs. He relishes learning about new places and adapting to the new environments he experiences. When he’s not working, you might find Jace on a run, helping refresh and redesign a room.

description: Hello! Thanks for stopping by. I understand that buying and selling a home is one of the biggest decisions of your life and not just a transaction. name: Mike Blackmon
description: Mike is the Commercial Division Manager for the Berkshire Hathaway HS | Ambassador Real Estate company, serving the Omaha Metro, Nebraska and Iowa. With a background in sales, banking, and real estate, Mike is 'client-centric', - a 'matchmaker' for his clients and their real estate needs. Includes listing and selling brokerage, landlord AND tenant rep leasing, revitalization and/or re-purposing existing buildings, and new developments. Our Commercial Division has a very strong background and experience in all aspect of new development, construction management, project management, asset management, critical analyis of a building and/or an entire project for analyzing the project feasibility and potential profitability. Mike currently serves as Vice-Chair of the MRCIE (Midlands Regional Commercial Information Exchange) serving Nebraska and Iowa, beginning May1, 2017. Mike is a member of Governmental Affairs Committee for the Omaha Area Board of Realtors. Historically, Mike has been in consultative selling all of his life. Mike invested 12 years in the life insurance and employee benefits business, including financial planning, estate planning, and employee benefit planning, for the medium size business owners and high income earners. Mike earned his professional designation as a CLU in 1976 from The American College in Bryn Mawr, PA, which has proved time and again to be valuable background to assist his real estate clients. An opportunity arose to enter the banking business in a small town bank, where Mike learned all facets of banking, from the teller to the regulatory filings to agriculture, consumer, and commercial business lending. These two careers had a huge impact and fabulous background training for a career in real estate since 1981. Back in Omaha since 2000, Mike has increased his commercial sales, real estate investment analysis skills, and developement and asset management skills with hands-on involvement and counseling a myriad of diffferent experience level of investors and owner/users of commercial real estate. Mike works by referral. If you or your friends and/or associates have a project you are interested in, please feel free to contact Mike to see if we - The Project, Mike - or one of our Team, and You, are a 'Match'!! We love to help make a project come to life and become a success.

description: Born and raised in Fremont, NE, I left my home town in 1988 to start a business venture in Norfolk, NE. In 2005 we decided Nebraska was the place to raise a family and we moved home, and I continued my real estate career. Now I have a small team of realtors that work with me, and together we have a very well rounded group. From first time home buyers, to seasoned investors, land to commercial, we have the background to help you meet your real estate goals! My wonderful wife Wendy and I enjoy traveling, fine dining and spending time with family. We have 4 adult children, 3 dogs and not enough time to vacuum! In my spare time I'm a golf addict and I live and die with Cubs baseball and Husker Hoops and Football. I also enjoy playing around with the stock market with what little time I have. description: I started my real estate career in 2003 at small independent firm, and in 2008 I received my broker's license. In 2011 I joined Prudential Ambassador Real Estate which is now Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate. I want your service to be so fantastic that you will want to refer your friends and family; and every time you think of real estate, you think of me.

description: Welcome! As a Realtor and local business owner, executive and entrepreneur, I bring a unique blend of expertise, a strategic mindset, and a comprehensive understanding in navigating complex negotiations and contracts, ensuring favorable outcomes for clients. I am passionate about helping individuals and families find their dream homes and make sound real estate investments. Let's connect and discuss how I can assist you in achieving your real estate goals. Whether you're a buyer, seller, or investor, I am committed to delivering outstanding results and exceeding your expectations. Home is Where Your Story Begins - Ken

name: Alyson Roberts
description: A Nebraska native and licensed real estate agent, Alyson Roberts, is a member of the ‘All Metro Real Estate Group’, which is part of the Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate. She specializes in selling real estate in the greater Omaha area. Alyson has a deep connection with Omaha, being a fourth generation Omahian and fifth generation Nebraskan. She loves the feel of Omaha being a big-little city, and wants to show her clientele the magic of her hometown. Prior to her professional career in real estate, Aly has lived and traveled all over the world. Receiving her Bachelor degree from the University of Denver. Eventually, she found her way back to Omaha and spent the last ten years managing storage facilities. After a decade of speaking with and taking care of people on a daily basis about the process of buying and selling their homes, she eventually decided to take her knowledge and expertise to switch her career to real estate. Aly believes strongly in reusing, recycling, and renovating. She looks forward to giving some of the historic places of Omaha a new life. She wants every home to be given a grand future and looks forward to matching the right home to the right clients. To find that right individual that will love their new home and appreciate it. Aly’s goal is to devote her energy to her clients to find the home that will best suit their needs, and give them an unrivaled home buying experience.

description: MEET ANNALI & The Will2Way® Promise! Annali is hardworking, enthusiastic and dedicated to serving others! Annali enjoys working with all people in all walks in life and represents a handful of active investors who entrust her with their home flips and large rental portfolios. Professionalism, Equal Opportunity & Participation Committee, Chair of Nebraska REALTORS® Assoc. Statewide Professional Standards Review Committee & also holds the At Home With Diversity Certification, Sellers Representative Specialist Designation®, Real Estate Negotiation Expert Certification, Military Relocation Professional Designation® & Real Estate Investment Specialist Certification. When you hire Annali, you are getting so much more than a salesperson. You’re hiring a zealous REALTOR® who will pour her heart and soul into making the way through your real estate transaction! Annali created the Will2Way® Promise - she holds herself to a higher standard; being strict about good ethics, having the needed knowledge to navigate the deal & the best tech available to best serve her clients.  She stays updated on local laws and customs, is armed with 15+ years of experience, cultivated highly effective negotiating tactics & thoroughly enjoys assisting clientele with questions and unique needs. All you need to do is "Express Your Will 2 Be Shown The Way!!" & you'll have you're trusted real estate guide for life!

When my husband and I started investing in real estate to diversify our portfolio, I discovered a passion that I wanted to pursue further. Being in real estate gives me the satisfaction of helping individuals through every stage of their lives, and truly makes me feel like I am part of a community. My business is built on communication, dedication and hard work. I enjoy working with and meeting new people. I look forward to working with you to navigate through this experience to make it as stress free and rewarding as possible. When I’m not working I enjoy spending time with my family consisting of my husband and two little boys. I enjoy golfing, exercising, and any activity I can do outdoors.

Whether you are looking to buy your first home or sell your current property, looking for an investment property. I have a proven track record of success in marketing homes, finding the perfect investment properties, and helping my clients navigate the buying and selling process with ease. My goal is to make every transaction smooth, stress-free, fun, and educating for my clients. In addition to my career in real estate, I am also a local radio host for The Big Party Morning Show on Channel 941. This has given me the opportunity to connect with members of the community on a personal level and further deepen my knowledge of the neighborhoods in Omaha. I use my gift of marketing and promotion to help my clients through the process for maximum results. I understand the importance of effective marketing and utilize my expertise to get the best possible outcome for my clients. Outside of work, I am a proud husband and father to three beautiful dogs - two goldendoodles and a poodle. As a family-oriented person, I understand the importance of finding the perfect home for your loved ones and I am committed to helping you achieve that goal. Let me put my passion and expertise to work for you and help you find the home of your dreams. description: My goal is to offer exceptional real estate services whether you are buying, selling, investing, or building! My passion to educate clients, communicate quickly, provide clear information throughout the entire process, and facilitate a smooth & efficient transaction are my primary objectives! As a retired 1st grade teacher (32 years) I am able to multi-task, navigate various scenarios that may arise, and establish a clear plan to get to closing on time! Investing in yourself, your future, your family, and your short term & long term goals, will become my priority! I am knowledgeable, concise, hard working, compassionate, ambitious, honest, and dedicated. I firmly believe in working as a team for your benefit & putting your needs & wants in real estate first!

name: Shari Grimes
description: Raised in a large family in rural Iowa, I learned early on the value of hard work, perseverance and the importance of taking care of those around us. When I decided to make a change, Real Estate felt like a natural fit. My passions have always been taking care of people, creating a welcoming home environment and creative marketing / business strategies. I use these passions daily in my business. During the past 9+ years as a Realtor, I’ve been fortunate to have listed and sold homes throughout the Omaha Metro area. There is nothing quite like seeing a client’s eyes light up when they’ve found that perfect home or sensing their relief / excitement when they’ve received an offer on their home. I feel truly blessed to have found a career that allows me to be involved with my clients in a personal and impactful manner. It has been my experience that clients want someone they can trust to guide them through the process. I would be honored to help you or your friends and family find your dream home. Please contact me if you are interested in buys, selling, building, or investing in real estate.

name: Ann Townsend
description: As part of a relocated family, Ann has the first-hand experience with all the emotions, stress and logistics of moving a household, family and life to a new city. With a father who is a disabled veteran, transitioning military families in and out of our community is her sweet spot. Ann and her husband used to own a real estate portfolio of 48 units until she decided to go into residential real estate in 2011. Now, with a real estate background, relocation experience, an accounting degree and community involvement, Ann is able to sell Omaha, find the right house and ensure her clients get the best prices for the house they are buying or selling. Ann uses all the tools available to ensure her clients get into their dream homes. Known for her honesty, integrity and dedication, Kathy always has the best interest of her buyers and sellers at heart. Ann works with the Omaha Chamber of Commerce, Omaha Children’s Hospital, Creighton University HCOB, ABIDE, Catholic Charities, JDRF and Little White Dog Rescue "I am an agent you can trust to be at your side during the entire home-buying process. Exceeding expectations, responsive communication and personal customer service are hallmarks of my business. This high-level of service is what you can expect to receive as I use all tools available to ensure you end up in your dream home. Because you MATTER, I am always on your side." – Ann Townsend

name: Dylon Deshazo
description: We are the Deshazo Team, a husband and wife team of two dedicated realtors at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices.  We are devoted to helping both buyers and sellers in making their transactions go as smoothly as possible.  We are passionate in our field and making sure you find the right home to fit your needs or get the best value for your sale.  We can ensure you an open line of communication throughout the entire process and we are here to answer any questions along the way.  We can provide you with the latest market trends and activity and provide daily home searches. We live with our two daughters Alyssa and Aubrey in Papillion, Nebraska and serve all surrounding areas.  We believe that family is important and strive to work around your schedules and find the perfect home to fit your family's needs, just as we would want for ours.  We hope to help you in your next move!

name: Katie Adams
job_title: VP Corporate Relocation Services  and Business Development

name: Danni Huston
description: : I came to the Real Estate Industry with 10 years of Mortgage loan experience. With a combination of my mortgage knowledge and my bubbly personality, I help my clients through a very smooth transition through the buying or selling process. My clients don't have anything to worry about with me, as I'm there with them every step of the way and through every life change! In my personal life, I have a loving husband, our dog Tobe, who thinks he's a celebrity, and our cat Bella who believes she runs the house. When we aren't working, my husband and I are out at the lake sailing and part-taking in water sports!

name: Judy Kramer
description: Licensed Realtor in Nebraska since 2012; in real estate since mid-2011 Strong financial background with 12 years experience; previously held securities license and continue to hold life and health licenses Certified Military Relocation Professional (MRP) with extensive experience dealing with military 15 years in Human Resources with Professional in Human Resources (PHR) certification and Certified Employee Benefits Professional (CEBS) Notary Public BSBA Management

name: Tasha Moss
description: I love the relationships I have built in this business over the past 21 years and I'm very fortunate to have a strong referral-based business with over 95% of my business coming from past clients and referrals. I am a team leader for one of the top teams in the United States, ranked in the Top 5 Real Estate Teams for Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Real Estate in the U S. I have sold 1000’s of homes & pride myself in maintaining a higher level of understating of the real estate market & I quite typically forecast changes in the pipeline for my clients. This is something that comes with years of experience and the wherewithal to see the changes by watching market trends across the country and speaking to other top level agents I associate with in other markets. Areas of real estate expertise include: 1st time buyers, new construction, investors, military relocation, condominium & townhome sales and luxury real estate. Let me help you make the RIGHT MOVE!

name: Shelly Anderson
description: My mission is to provide a 5-star client experience in the home buying and selling process. I have exceptional client service, ground breaking marketing ideas, attention to detail and strong negotiating skills. My primary objective when I partner with you on selling your home is to achieve the highest net proceeds in the shortest amount of time utilizing staging, high-end photography and strategic marketing. When buying a home, I guide my clients step-by-step through the home buying process, assist diligently in your home search by providing many options and negotiate strongly on your behalf. Please contact me at 402-612-5410 for all of your real estate needs!

name: Kara Bellino
description: With her genuine nature, eye for design and love for Omaha - Kara Bellino strives to exceed expectations with each & every client! Her patient mindset & calm demeanor will carry you effortlessly through negotiations making the process exciting from start to finish. No home search or home sale is ever the same, and Kara is always up to the challenge of matching her clients with the perfect house that just feels like home. “What I adore most is getting to know you. Everyone has their unique story and the fun part about my job is, I get to learn that story! It is so rewarding to contribute to someone else’s happiness and to help them find the perfect place to call home.” Earning her real estate license in 2015, Kara’s diverse real estate resume enhances her knowledge in the industry and is a true asset to her clients. Having flipped 20+ homes she knows how to creatively improve spaces & understands the investment side of real estate. When Kara is not showing homes, she is working alongside her husband Vince, acquiring single & multi-family rental properties and even recently played a key role in designing apartments from the ground up! From sun up to sun down Kara is immersed in the real estate life and she loves it. Kara is also a proud mom of three little ones who definitely keep her on her toes… just as much as the ever-changing real estate market!

name: Steve VanHerpen
description: Bringing extensive knowledge of the real estate market. I offer all my clients an unmatched level of service. My formal education and training added with many years of purchasing, owning and selling property allows me to excel at all levels needed to finalize a real estate transaction. Growing up in a military family, I know what it takes to move from place to place every three to four years. I also know all the stresses moving from place to place can cause and know what it takes to eliminate those stresses. I have lived in the Omaha, Bellevue, and Papillion areas for over 19 years and have a vast knowledge of the area. If you’re looking for a realtor that is willing to work endlessly to ensure your home buying and selling needs are taken care of, look no further.

name: Matt Donahue
description: I grew up in the Westside area and I've spent my entire life in Omaha.  I obtained by Master's Degree in 2012 and spent my early career in higher education as an academic and financial advisor.  However, I had a passion for real estate and joined BHHS Ambassador Real Estate in 2016.  Since then I've focused on residential sales and multi-family investments. As an investor myself, I  have a passion helping clients explore the benefits of real estate either finding their first home, forever home or using real estate as an investment vehicle and getting setup for retirement. Outside of work I enjoy spending quality time with my son, Cal, daughter, Mayley, and beautiful wife Amanda. I love sports and grew up playing hockey and baseball but when I have free time you can usually find me teeing up at a golf course.

name: Jason McCune
description: Meet Jason Jason’s hard work, personality and true passion for business makes him a standout.  Well connected to the community, Jason provides top of the line service to every client whether they are buying, selling or just considering options.  Jason’s background in residential developments includes multiple areas in the community and being part of a successful real estate development family that has prospered for over 50 years in the area, has given Jason the knowledge, integrity and expertise needed to provide the best service. Keeping his clients’ goals front and foremost is important, keeping them fully informed throughout the process, making the transaction smooth from contract, closing and beyond.  Jason will be your lifetime realtor.

name: Klaire Cross
description: Klaire is in her first year of real estate. She is also the executive assistant to team leader Gail Hunter. Klaire graduated from Lewis Central High School, after she completed a Bachelor's of Communication degree from Graceland University. Klaire played collegiate volleyball at Graceland University in Lamoni Iowa as well as coached men's and women's volleyball the past four years. Klaire grew up in Council Bluffs her whole life, she loves to spend time with her family and friends around town and enjoys the outdoors. One of Klaire’s favorites is playing and spending time with her three dogs, Django the Siberian husky, Nevaeh the goldendoodle and Kalea the Doberman pinscher. She can be reached at 402-206-4589 or Klaire.Cross@BHHSamb.com.

name: Brian Wilson
description: As a real estate professional at BHHS Ambassador Real Estate, I understand the importance of working with a professional agent who will have your best interests at heart. With over 25 years of experience in real estate and 22 of those specializing in new construction, you can rely on me for great advice, whether it is guiding you seamlessly through your home building project or helping you buy or sell an existing home. I proudly represent Al Belt Custom Homes, one of the Omaha areas’ premier builders. I believe in customer service above all else – believing that every individual deserves my full commitment and loyalty. As a local resident, I know the area and can give you access to information that you will never find on the Internet! I am supported by a company that understands the customer’s needs in a dynamic and rapidly changing real estate environment. This enables me to offer the most powerful real estate services to home buyers and sellers, including relocation services, financing, title insurance and much more. Give me a call, or send me an email and let me put my expertise to work for you today!

name: Julie Deshazo
description: We are the Deshazo Team, a husband and wife team of two dedicated realtors at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices.  We are devoted to helping both buyers and sellers in making their transactions go as smoothly as possible.  We are passionate in our field and making sure you find the right home to fit your needs or get the best value for your sale.  We can ensure you an open line of communication throughout the entire process and we are here to answer any questions along the way.  We can provide you with the latest market trends and activity and provide daily home searches. We live with our two daughters Alyssa and Aubrey in Papillion, Nebraska and serve all surrounding areas.  We believe that family is important and strive to work around your schedules and find the perfect home to fit your family's needs, just as we would want for ours.  We hope to help you in your next move!

name: Chelsea Heather
description: I believe every real estate transaction should be simplified and transparent, backed with expertise and support, and driven by your specific goals and dreams. I provide no-strings-attached consultations and complimentary home valuations to any potential client. Whether you're buying your first home or your 5th, whether you are selling, downsizing, investing, or anything in between, I prioritize education on the process, market updates and standards, valuation, and strategy. Real estate transactions are complex and involve several moving parts, and it's my job to stand by you every step of the way and help navigate you to the future you are dreaming of. Ever since I was a child, I've loved looking at houses, and I would dream about what my perfect house would look like. I have always been fascinated with architectural history and design; a fascination which later led me to study architectural drafting and interior design at The New York Institute of Art and Design. While designing unique interiors for each client, it became clear to me then that a house is not a home without someone to love it, and I began to pursue a life in real estate. Outside of my love of real estate and design, I am also passionate about painting, volunteering, playing music, and stargazing. Call me for a consultation or free home valuation today!

name: Monserrat Avalos Pantoja
description: I, Monserrat, am excited to help you, my client throughout your journey in finding your dream home! Waking up in an accommodating home and environment is the key to making memories, grow, and nurture together as a family. The journey there should not be a problem more nonetheless a stressing experience. My goal is to be with you along the way by offering my dedication, aspiration, and proficiency to your goal. Your goal is my goal! Yo, Monserrat, estoy emocionada para ayudar a usted, mi cliente a lo largo de su búsqueda en encontrar el hogar de su sueños! Al despertar en un cómodo hogar y ambiente es la llave para hacer memorias, crecer, y nutrir juntos en familia. La búsqueda no debe de ser un problema mas mucho menos una experiencia estresante. Mi meta es estar con usted durante el proceso ofreciendo mi dedicación, aspiración, y habilidades a su meta. Su meta es mi meta!

name: Brian Thomas
description: BRIAN THOMAS  in 1971, after graduating from college with majors in speech and real estate (proving I know everything there is to know about real estate) I went into residential sales.  I now have 50 years exerience in sales, management, and owning my own company . . . I´m so good!  Charismatic, handsome, sharp dresser, father of 3 sons . . . and still married to their mother.  As a second generation REALTOR real estate has always been part of my life. I am currently the General Manager at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate.

name: Courtney Goodman
description: Born and raised in St. Louis, Courtney Goodman received his BS from The University of Kansas where he majored in Journalism. Courtney has been deeply involved in all things real estate for over 20 years: as an investor, project manager, teacher, coach, non-profit board member, Government Relations Chair, and Realtor. Since 2015, Courtney has proudly contributed his real estate acumen, enthusiasm, and vast experience to Berkshire Hathaway where his true passion lies in protecting his clients’ equity and hard-earned money. Courtney’s unwavering advocacy and commitment to his clients is evident in his prompt, open, and detailed communication style, negotiation expertise, and guidance. In his free time, Courtney’s interests include tennis, basketball, travel, home improvements, and spending time with family and friends.

name: Kristina Oreskovich
description: Grounded by her Cornhusker roots, Kristina understands what makes Nebraska a special place to call home.  Her friendly and outgoing nature, coupled with exceptional communication skills, allows her to connect effortlessly with clients. As a devoted wife and mother of two wonderful kids, Kristina cherishes her connections with family and friends. With an entrepreneurial spirit, Kristina founded the company, Omaha School of Music and Dance (OSMD), which after 10 years of ownership, sold recently to her trusted lead instructor. She also has been an active Residential & Commercial Real Estate Investor for years and is excited to dive fully into the Omaha real estate market. With Kristina you can trust that your Real Estate goals will be met with the utmost dedication, professionalism, and touch of joy. Through hard-work, creativity and open lines of communication Kristina brings a wealth of knowledge and a seamless, enjoyable Real Estate journey to you. Her passion for Real Estate investing and her desire to help her clients navigate the exciting world of real estate are true assets.  Kristina can guide you towards the most lucrative business/investment opportunities and help you maximize your real estate portfolios potential. Contact her today and let her make your dream home or investment a reality!

name: Trish Thompson
description: SRES - Senior Real Estate Specialist SRS - Seller Representative Specialist RENE - Real Estate Negotiation Expert ABR - Accredited Buyer Representative PSA - Pricing Strategy Advisor - Trish Thompson's passion for unprecedented client service coupled with an expert knowledge of buying and selling real estate has helped her build a reputation as an invaluable ally in helping her clients reach their real estate goals. With real estate being an on-the-go work environment, Trish is an energetic results-driven achiever, with a genuine passion for the real estate industry and does not stop moving until her clients needs are exceeded. As a long time resident in the Omaha metro area, few things bring Trish more satisfaction than helping people in her community invest in their future through their next home. Trish works closely with her husband and real estate partner Brett Thompson.  Prior to working in real estate, Trish served with great pride as a salon owner and hair color specialist for over 25 years. "The best part of my real estste business is still the personal connection with my clients!" WHAT WOULD SURPRISE YOU ABOUT ME? "I have resided in 8 states in the USA. Indiana, Michigan, Washington, Texas, Alabama, Colorado, Arkansas. Last but not least Nebraska for the past 23 years. If you want to know what it's like to move and start over in a new city, I'm your expert" FAMILY AND HOBBIES When not spending time helping clients, Trish and Brett enjoy traveling and dining with family or dear friends, scuba diving, cooking and eating Mexican cuisine. What's our favorite restaurant? Our own kitchen!

name: Holly Swirczek
description: MEET HOLLY As a Nebraska native and a seasoned professional, I value the trust my clients place in me, and I strive every day to exceed their expectations. I pay attention to the details, and am available for my clients during this process of buying or selling a home. Outside of  my real estate career, I enjoy my life near Fontenelle Forest, go jogging on the forest trails and foster children. The best thing I can do for you is hear what you want, see where you need me, and promise to make your home my highest priority.

name: Melissa Gerdes
description: Melissa Gerdes, a seasoned professional with two decades of experience in the social work industry, embarked on a new chapter by leveraging her passion for real estate. After acquiring her Nebraska real estate license, Melissa's journey in the Omaha market has been defined by her unwavering commitment to client satisfaction. Known for treating clients like family, Melissa's approach is characterized by friendliness, openness, and compassion. Clients appreciate her accessibility and the assurance that their needs will always take precedence. Melissa's reputation for integrity is a cornerstone in guiding clients through the complexities of property transactions, instilling trust in every step of the buying or selling process. Melissa's extensive professional network proves invaluable for clients, whether navigating challenging loans, connecting with reliable remodeling teams, or finding the ideal commercial location. Beyond conventional real estate services, Melissa goes the extra mile by covering professional cleaning and moving expenses, as well as providing complimentary staging services to alleviate the stresses of the real estate journey. Recognizing the transformative impact of a dedicated real estate agent, Melissa draws on her years of property transactions to simplify the process for her clients. Her commitment is reflected not only in professional endeavors but also in personal touches, ensuring each client receives the attention and care she would expect from her own real estate agent. A native of California, Melissa now calls Omaha home, residing with her exceptional and talented children. Fluent in both English and Spanish, Melissa's multicultural proficiency enhances her ability to connect with a diverse clientele. Embracing the local lifestyle, she finds joy in reading, decorating, gardening, baking, and exploring new destinations with her family. For Melissa, the real estate industry is not just about transactions; it's about forging lasting relationships that extend well beyond the closing of a deal. Her love for the Omaha community and its offerings resonates in every aspect of her life, both personally and professionally.

name: Omaha Fuller Group
description: Meet Our Team DON FULLER Associate Broker / Manager Don has been a real estate broker for over 40 years, serving the greater Omaha area and surrounding communities. As group leader, Don brings many years of knowledge and first-hand experience to his team. His resume includes real estate sales and development, owner/partnership in several real estate-related businesses, and new home construction - building over 500 homes in the Omaha area. Achieving designations such CRS, GRI and Graduate of Builders Institute, as well as his broad experience in finance and marketing have contributed to making Don one of the top producing agents in the city of Omaha. Attending national real estate conferences and focusing on the latest technology and innovations in marketing are only some of the ways Don continues his “commitment to excellence”. Over the years Don has mentored some of Omaha’s finest agents. He believes in giving back to the community, helping others attain their goals and building life-long friendships along the way. JAN FULLER Licensed Realtor® HSR Certified Home Stager & Redesigner A licensed realtor in the Omaha Fuller Group, Jan also brings another significant benefit to the group. She has been a certified professional home stager/re-designer in the Omaha area for many years. With staged properties selling 50% faster and up to 30% more, Jan brings her staging services and knowledge as a complimentary service to all Omaha Fuller Group listings. With a history in the new construction industry, Jan enjoys exercising her decorating talents by making new construction home selections for models and spec homes for builders in the Omaha area, as well as guiding clients through the selection process. Her staging experience also carries over into this area by staging and furnishing model homes. “When you love what you do, you’ll never have to work a day in your life”. And Jan loves what she does! CORY FULLER Licensed Realtor® I have been a licensed Realtor in Nebraska since 2004, have sold over $100 Million in residential real estate and have been previously ranked in the top 15% of all Realtors in the nation.  I have an absolute passion for helping both home buyers and sellers reach their goal of moving on to the next step of their lives.  Working with clients in ALL price ranges, whether it be a $100K or $800K home, each transaction receives equal importance. I am here to make the process simple, smooth and enjoyable and utilize the latest in technology on all fronts to make it happen. I also believe strongly in giving back to our community. It was my privilege to be involved in raising money for The Sunshine Kids Foundation, a wonderful organization who's sole focus is giving kids who are battling cancer every day, the childhood memories they deserve through trips, events and activities nationwide with other kids who have similar challenges.  I have raised over $90,000 for this organization, by sponsoring a huge annual fundraiser called Marchi Gras, a two night live music festival, at which all of the proceeds have gone to The Sunshine Kids Foundation. JASON FULLER Photographer Technology Consultant Owner of Lifestyle 360, Jason is a member of Professional Photographers of America and was certified as a Google Street View Trusted Photographer in January of 2018. He has a diverse background in photography; graphics, web, and UI/Ux design; video production; music arrangements and performance; and collaboration science. Jason has always had a passion for technology and photography and obtained his Master's degree in 2009 from the college of Information Systems and Quantitative Analysis at the University of Nebraska.

name: Carla Vigness
description: I moved from MA to NE about 28 years ago and have been working in sales and marketing since. My goal is always to make my clients’ experience a positive one while making sure to have fun in the process. As your realtor, you will always be my top priority and I will be with you every step of the way during the entire buying or selling process. When I am able, I love to travel to New York City to visit my son, Brady, who is an aspiring actor on Broadway!

name: Didi Pache
description: I became licensed in 2010 after an extensive history in luxury sales & executive management. Born in the Los Angeles area, I have acquired, sold, built, remodeled & leased homes in the Los Angeles and San Francisco Bay Areas, Dallas, Boston and Omaha, where I have lived since 1996. Known for an exuberant personality, I am easy to work with and always willing to take the time to discuss my client’s questions and concerns. I have first-hand experience in the relocation process. In addition, I maintain a strong educational foundation having earned The Graduate, REALTOR® Institute Designation (GRI), providing a more in-depth training in legal/regulatory issues, technology, professional standards, and the sales process as well as the Military Resource Professional Certificate (MRP) and Veterans Administration Loan Certified (VALC). Married for 34+ years with two sons. My husband was a Navy carrier fighter pilot. Our oldest is a Marine veteran having served in Afghanistan and my youngest is a pilot in the Navy flying P-8’s. In my spare time, I enjoy travelling, scuba diving, and reading.

name: Nic Luhrs
description: Meet Nic Nic is a real estate and investment professional with a background in team management, business ownership, and valuation. Having owned and operated several businesses; including retails stores and property management. Nic brings a unique approach to best strategize your home selling and buying experience. He first found his interest in the world of real estate through investing in rental properties.  He treats every client as if it were family; keeping their best interests in mind.  He has now taken this interest along with his expertise to guide his clients through a seamless and stress free process. He develops strong, long lasting relationships with his clients.  Nic doesn’t work on transactions, he works on relationships and guarantees you will enjoy working with him. You will experience a greater sense of trust through the streamlined and thorough processes that Nic uses to oversee every step of your real estate endeavors.

name: Mary Thommi CRS GRI SRES ePro
description: Omaha, Nebraska's Premier Realtor & Relocation Specialist with a CRS, GRI & SRES Designation (Only 4% of the Realtors in the United States have a CRS Designation) Associated with the #1 eal Estate company in Omaha. Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Leading Edge Award Winner 2021 Berkshire Hatahway HomeServices Leading Edge Award Winner 2020 Previously with CBSHome Real Estate - Was Outstanding Performer- Platinum Circle 2004-2015 Member of Council of Residential Specialist Member of Graduate Realtors Institute Memeber of Senior Residential Specialist Member of the National Association of Realtors Member of the Women's Council of Realtors Membr of the Omaha Area Board of Realtors Member of St. Wenceslaus Parish I enjoy my Faith, Family, Friends & Tennis. BUT MOST OF ALL BEING A MOTHER & A REALTOR.

name: Staci Mueller
description: MEET STACI Staci Mueller is a passionate and energized REALTOR® for Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate in Omaha, NE. Consistently a Top 10 producing Individual Agent year after year, Staci has been serving the entire metro Omaha area as a full time agent since 2008. She has extensive experience in the acreage and luxury markets, as well as serving buying and selling clients with a gamut of needs from first time home buyers, to retirees, to recreational hunting and lake interests, investment opportunities, and everything in between.

name: Amanda Martin
description: I started out in real estate in 2014 as an assistant to Realtor. This allowed me to learn the ins & outs on the backside of the business. After a year of being an assistant, I decided to take the leap of getting licensed! I haven’t looked back! I help people at many different points in their life from the first-time home buyers to the empty nester looking to downsize. (Or an investor looking to start building a portfolio) I take pride in helping people make the biggest financial decision of their life! There is no bigger compliment then knowing I have become the agent of choice for many different families. (I have even helped 4 generations in ONE family) I’d LOVE to help YOU with any of your real estate needs. I continually work to improve my client experience and keep educated with current marketing strategies, construction trends, market movements, and home values. I love what I do and strive to always satisfy my clients wants, needs and expectations.

name: Erb Real Estate Group
description: Founded by Team Leader JD Erb, our real estate group is dedicated to providing a high level of customer service and expertise to our clients. ERB Group is a team at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate in Omaha, Nebraska. We have sold and purchased over $150 million in Omaha real estate. We partner with several professionals within the industry to serve you best including lenders, interior design, new construction builder, insurance and more. Let's talk homes.

name: Shannon Leisey
description: As a top producing agent in the area, I'm very fortunate to have a strong referral-based business with over 95% of my business coming from past clients and referrals. I believe this speaks volumes to the positive experiences that my clients have while working with me to buy or sell their homes -- they trust me to take care of their friends and family. I cherish my role as the Team Leader for Suite Properties Group and have been licensed since 2007. In that time, I have helped hundreds of families buy and sell homes in the Omaha Metro and surrounding areas. My office at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate is the largest real estate office in Nebraska, which greatly assists me with not only marketing my listings to the other top producers in the area but to serve as a resource for finding the ‘HOT' new listings for my buyers before they hit the market. At the end of the day, my goal is to leave you with a smile and more money in your pocket than if you worked with another Realtor. I’m doing more than just selling houses in Nebraska, I’m helping you bring your dream home to life. Designations & Attributes: Successfully Closed 675+ homes, Over 160+ Million in Volume BHHS Relocation Team Luxury Collection Specialist Certified Master Negotiation Expert Brookfield Global Relocation Certification Cartus Relocation Specialist BGRS Certified in Marketing Assistance Professional Stagers President's Circle:  Top 5% of Entire BHHS Global Network of Realtors Chairman's Circle--Top 2% of Entire BHHS Global Network of Realtors

name: Sam Ganarajah
description: Born in Sri Lanka, Ajith “Sam” Ganarajah graduated from Emporia State University as a Dean’s List student with a Bachelor of Science in finance and a member of the TKE Fraternity. He has spent the last two decades as a proud, dynamic and productive Nebraskan. Sam’s deep and abiding love for the people of Omaha, combined with a breath of insight and experience that spans multiple industries and continents have helped him enjoy great professional and personal success. name: Lynette Dole
description: My name is Lynette Dole a Realtor at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate and proud member of Team O As a graduate of Randall School of Real Estate and a licensed realtor since 2012, I pride myself on providing exceptional service that goes above and beyond for my clients. Prior to embarking on my career in real estate, I owned a successful gift basket business for 13 years. My experience as a business owner has instilled in me a strong work ethic, attention to detail, and the ability to work well under pressure. I am licensed in Nebraska and Iowa, and have a wealth of knowledge about the local real estate market, which I leverage to help both buyers and sellers make informed decisions. My passion for real estate, coupled with my commitment to delivering the best possible results, has earned me a reputation as a dedicated and trustworthy realtor. When I'm not working, you can find me cheering on the Kansas City Chiefs, playing games, boating, fishing, or spending time with my family and friends. I am also an active member of MOBA, Women's Council of Realtors, OABR, and SWIAR. Through these organizations, I have gained valuable insights and strengthened my network, which ultimately benefits my clients. I have earned several designations, including Graduate Realtor Institute (GRI), Residential Investment Specialist (RIS) , Military Relocation Professional (MRP), Pricing Strategy Advisor (PSA) and Certified New Construction Specialist (CNCS), which demonstrate my commitment to ongoing education and professional development. These designations have equipped me with the tools and knowledge to offer my clients cutting-edge insights and expertise, delivering the best possible results. If you're looking for a realtor who is passionate, knowledgeable, and dedicated to helping you achieve your real estate goals, look no further.  I am committed to providing you with an unparalleled level of service, and I look forward to working with you.

name: Jessica Dembinski
description: Jessica grew up living in several cities all over the country, and her family landed in Omaha right before she started high school. As a graduate from Skutt Catholic, she began to learn the value of hard work and at a young age discovered that one of her favorite things to do was help others. She moved to Minneapolis, MN and graduated with a Bachelor’s degree in Music Performance from North Central University. After getting married and having their first child, Jessica and her husband Nicholas decided to move to Omaha to raise and establish their family in a city they knew and loved. They’ve lived in the Omaha metro since 2016 and have established themselves in their neighborhood as go-to people for a friendly smile and help with shoveling the front walk. Jessica is passionate about all things real estate. From home organization and staging to marketing and salesmanship-Jessica will go above and beyond what you are looking for with you realtor. With over 12 years of strong successful sales and leadership experience, resulting in best in class service to customers, Jessica always works towards consistent growth, industry-leading customer service, and attentive listening-to walk with you on your homeownership journey.

name: Amy Schinco
description: MEET AMY Buy with Confidence, Sell with Success! My passion has always been helping others. I have found that being a Real Estate Agent is so satisfying as there are so many important parts to this process. Treating my clients like family is my guiding principle to help them navigate the buying and selling process seamlessly. I am committed to listening to your needs and utilizing my expert negotiating skills to ensure a successful transaction. I have a team of professional service providers to assist you including stagers, painters, designers, handymen, inspectors, insurance agents, and mortgage lenders. I am thorough, communicative, detail oriented, and enthusiastic. I will be alongside you every step of the way!

name: Carl Griffin
description: I'm a lifelong resident of Omaha with a passion to serve the community and I can provide you with access to information that you can never find on the internet!  I'm here to deliver a quality experience for home buyers, sellers, as well as real estate investors.  I'm a professional whom you can count on to serve your interests with integrity. Call, text, or e-mail me anytime and let me put my expertise and the MRG Realty Group team to work for you today!

name: Ben Proctor
description: I am happy to say that this is now 20 years in the real estate industry. I have been lucky to acquire expansive knowledge in several areas of residential real estate including relocation, development, sales, marketing, and management. Since 2004, I have been involved in the sales, marketing, branding, and selling of multi-family developments in Omaha, Nebraska's growing urban market. While being heavily involved in Omaha's urban market I have had the pleasure to be a planning partner in events such as the Downtown Living Tour. As I continue to advance my career I continue to strive to achieve short term goals like building a leading residential sales business, expanding management services, and continuing to create effective and modern sales approach for residential developers. Long term I strive to be recognized as a go to resource in the residential real estate industry and as a contributor that has made an impact on the community and those in need.

name: Jenn Bennett
description: Jenn Bennett has been serving the Omaha area as a full-time, top producing Realtor for over 20 years. She is well-versed in all areas of residential real estate: Listing Specialist, First-Time HomeBuyers, Luxury Market, New Construction, Relocation, Downsizing, Real Estate Investment, Condos/Townhomes, Acreages, and more. "Whether you're considering buying, selling, building, or investing, or even if you're just in the planning stages for next year, I'm here for you! 🤍 With over two decades of experience in Omaha's Real Estate market, I promise, as your trusted FOREVER agent, to put my expertise to work, ensuring you achieve the best results. Let's make your Real Estate dreams a reality! 🤝" ~Jenn

name: John Mahoney
description: I have been born and raised in Lincoln, and while I spent a very short time out side of Lincoln, I have spent my entire life here. I got into Real Estate after leaving the Army and after selling my bar down town. I have now been selling real estate for 20+ years, and enjoying every moment of it. In years past I have been a top producing agent, and plan on keeping that status going into the future. When I'm not selling Lincoln, I am spending time with my daughter, or going out with friends to enjoy the Husker games!

name: The Georges
description: WE ARE READY TO SERVE YOU! MIKE Experience ·  Licensed in Nebraska & Iowa ·  Founder/Owner, EGA Real Estate, LLC, & Nettle Hill Real Estate, LLC, Papillion, NE; Past Vice-President, MG Real Estate Investments, Inc., Houston, PA ·  US Marine Corps Officer, Retired ·  Strategic Planner, Division/Deputy Division Chief, US Strategic Command, Offutt AFB, NECommunity Involvement ·  Sarpy County Planning Commissioner (2014-2021) ·  Member, Nebraska Planning & Zoning Association (NPZA) ·  Board Member, Metro Omaha Property Owner’s Association (MOPOA) (2014-2020) ·  Past Elder, local area Church Education ·  Graduate, American Society of Home Inspectors School (ASHI), Des Plaines, IL ·  Master of Business Administration (MBA)Creighton University, Omaha, NE, 2010 ·  Bachelor of Science, Economics, US Naval Academy, Annapolis, MD, 1988 DEANNA Experience ·  Licensed in Nebraska ·  Co-Owner, EGA Real Estate, LLC, Papillion, NE ·  Elementary Education Teacher, 1995-1999 ·  USAA Advisory Panel Board Member, 2007-2009 ·  USMC Spouse’s Key Volunteer Advisor Community Involvement ·  Parent Volunteer, Bellevue Elementary School ·  Parent Volunteer, Platteview Central Junior High and Platteview Senior High School ·  Member/Volunteer, local area Church Education ·  Master of Education/Human Relations, Northern Arizona University, 1998 ·  Bachelor of Science, Elementary Education, East Carolina University, 1994 ·  SRES

name: Jill McGreer
description: Jill is an Omaha native with a love for the midwest. She has a passion for real estate and enjoys listening to her buyers' needs and helping them find the perfect place to call home. Her experience in sales and marketing gives her the edge needed to help her sellers get a quick sale and top dollar for their home.  Jill's level of customer care is unmatched in the industry, making her a key asset in every real estate transaction.  When she isn't working, you can find her watching volleyball, enjoying a lakeside bikeride, spending time with her family, or out to eat at one of the many local restaurants Omaha has to offer.

name: Mike George
description: More information about Mike Experience ·  Licensed in Nebraska & Iowa ·  Founder/Owner, EGA Real Estate, LLC, & Nettle Hill Real Estate, LLC, Papillion, NE; Past Vice-President, MG Real Estate Investments, Inc., Houston, PA ·  US Marine Corps Officer, Retired Strategic Planner, Division/Deputy Division Chief, US Strategic Command, Offutt AFB, NE Community Involvement ·  Sarpy County Planning Commissioner (2014-2021) ·  Member, Nebraska Planning & Zoning Association (NPZA) ·  Board Member, Metro Omaha Property Owner’s Association (MOPOA) (2014-2020) ·  Past Elder, local area Church Education ·  Graduate, American Society of Home Inspectors School (ASHI), Des Plaines, IL ·  Master of Business Administration (MBA)Creighton University, Omaha, NE, 2010 ·  Bachelor of Science, Economics, US Naval Academy, Annapolis, MD, 1988

name: Andrea Critser
description: Andrea strives to deliver client care and service at the highest level. With her extensive background in high-end customer service, Andrea applies her dedicated, top-notch service skills, natural attention to detail, and creative negotiation tactics to give you an unparalleled home buying or selling experience. Born in Orange County, California, Andrea moved to Nebraska at a young age. Her memorable experience with her real estate agent during that move inspired her to pursue real estate. She has resided in both Douglas and Sarpy County for over 30 years and enjoys assisting clients across the Metro area. Andrea volunteers with The Junior League of Omaha and serves as their Marketing Chair. In her free time, she enjoys traveling, cooking, and spending time with her two dogs, Rocky & Coco.

name: Lori Havens
description: Hi! I’m Lori Havens and I am thrilled to be part of the Hagestad Real Estate Group at Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate. A graduate of Creighton University, I’ve spent the past 15 years working in public relations, sales and marketing - all while raising my family in the Greater Omaha area. My love of people and passion for real estate drew me into the business. As a self-proclaimed homebody, I can appreciate the importance of finding that perfect home for you and/or your family. After all, life’s too short not to love the home you’re in! When I’m not hustling and bustling as a realtor, I enjoy spending time with my husband, Shane, and our three children. I’m a devoted soccer mom who loves to cook for family & friends and practice yoga whenever possible. In the market to buy or sell ? Keep me in mind. Let’s find your Happy Place!

name: Macey Incontro
description: Meet the Expert Welcome to partnership with Macey Incontro, Where Every Key Opens a World of Possibilities! As a Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate agent, Macey prides herself on her ability to provide world class, personalized service to her clients. Understanding every home, every client, every need is unique; she represents every transaction with integrity, honesty, and empathy. To her, creating lifetime memories and making her clients feel like family is why she got into this business. Macey brings a unique bonus of real value: 14 years of professional experience including such internationally-known brands as Gap Inc. to luxury brands like Serena & Lily in the San Francisco Bay Area. Her vast business knowledge in marketing, design and large-scale negotations combined with her passion for real estate makes her an ideal partner in all real estate transactions. Macey has managed a combined $500M+ over her 14 years business experience. She holds a BS degree in International Business from the University of Nebraska, studied Political Economic History and International Economics at Oxford University, England, as well as French Language & Business at CLA Besançon, France.

name: Jasmine Greenwaldt
description: Known for her creativity and determination, Jasmine brings a fresh approach to selling Real Estate in the Omaha Metro and Southwest Florida areas. With her savvy business style and her Masters Degree in Art, Jasmine is able to seamlessly merge her unique talents into a well-rounded, intelligent home buying and selling experience. Sometimes a client's perfect home cannot be found... it needs to be created. Her artistic vision to see the possibilities in a property make her client’s dream home come true. As an additional benet to her clients and The Key Group, Jasmine has expanded her love of Real Estate & investing to Southwest Florida. Jasmine is a licensed Florida Real Estate agent and proud Owner of Coastal Cabana, luxury vacation rentals. With years of new construction experience, she has the gift of being able to polish the diamonds in the rough into the most sought after homes - from framing to final finishes. Ask her about the possibilities of expanding your real estate portfolio! When Jasmine is not selling real estate you will find her painting in her home art studio and displaying her sought after works in local galleries, enjoying new local restaurants, reading or listening to a podcast, traveling and spending time with friends and family.

name: Skyler Bauer
description: Skyler Bauer represents clients throughout Nebraska. He will do everything in is power to ensure your experience with The Briley Team is second-to-none. Skyler completed his Bachelor’s of Science in Business Administration with an emphasis in marketing and advertising at Morningside College. While attending college he competed on the gridiron, winning four conference championships during his time as a Mustang. He brings that same passion and energy to his clients during the home buying and selling process. Whether you’re a first-time home buyer or investor, looking for a luxury property or selling one of your own, Skyler can help you successfully reach your goals.

name: Erica Madrid
description: Whether your goals are buying, selling or both, I can give you my advice as a professional Realtor. I pride myself in knowing the surrounding community where we live. I'm passionated about helping others and found my true calling in real estate serving my clients and guiding them through one of the biggest investments of their lives. Mission to provide quality service, personal attention to your needs, up-to-date information, real estate advisor while striving for client loyalty. I would appreciate the opportunity to help you make important real estate decisions and guide you through the entire process, please call me today or email me. I look forward to hearing from you! Hablo Espanol.. Ya sea que sus objetivos sean comprar, vender o ambos, puedo brindarle mi consejo como agente inmobiliario profesional. Me enorgullezco de conocer la comunidad circundante donde vivimos. Me apasiona ayudar a los demás y encontré mi verdadera vocación en el sector bienes raices sirviendo a mis clientes y guiándolos a través de una de las mayores inversiones de sus vidas. Misión brindar un servicio de calidad, atención personalizada a sus necesidades, información actualizada, asesor bienes raices buscando la fidelización de sus clientes. Apreciaría la oportunidad de ayudarlo a tomar decisiones de bienes raices importantes y guiarlo a través de todo el proceso , por favor llámeme hoy o envíeme un correo electrónico. ¡Espero escuchar de usted!

name: Marla Janak
description: “I’m in tune to with your real estate needs.” I am a licensed real estate agent with Berkshire Hathaway Home Services/Ambassador Real Estate. I have spent my life as an educator in the public schools and now specialize in coaching new home buyers and sellers as a realtor. I develop a strong trustworthy relationship with my clients by guiding them through one the of the most important financial decisions they will make in their lifetime. I have developed my communication skills by working with thousands of young musicians as an instrumental band director in the public schools for 30+ years. I also perform on stage as a professional trumpet player with many excellent performing groups and top-notch musicians. My experience includes working with all kinds of buyers and sellers since 2019.  I am licensed in the State of Nebraska and a member of the National Association of Realtors, Omaha Area Board of Realtors, Great Plains Multiple Listing Service and Nebraska Real Estate Association.  I look forward to helping you sell your home and/or buy your next home. I will do my best to make it a great experience. Senior Real Estate Specialist - SRES Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate Jennings Team Awards: Chairmans Circle - Diamond Small Teams -  2023 Chairman's Circle -Diamond Medium Teams - 2022 Top 25 Nationally GCI Volume Mid-Size Team 2021 Chairmans Circle 2021 Diamond Award Winner Medium Teams 2021 Oracle Award for Large Team Producer 2020 Pinnacle Award for Top Large Team Number of Transactions 2020 Summit Award for Team Productivity (#7) 2020 Shooting Star Awards for Number of Transactions & Production (Mid-Size/Large/Mega) 2020 TOP TEN NATIONALLY Number of Units Sold Mid-Size Team 2020 Chairman's Circle Diamond in the Berkshire Hathaway Network 2019 Top 100 (Units) in the Berkshire Hathaway Network 2019 Top 100 (GCI) in the Berkshire Hathaway Network 2019 Other : · Tri-M Music Honor Society Honorary Life Member – 2019 · Thirty Year Certificate-Nebraska Music Education Association-2019 · Schmitt Music “Educator of the Year” – 2018 · Inducted into the Omaha Sokol Polka Hall of Fame – 2012 Education: · Randall School of Real Estate – 2018 · Master of Arts Degree in Trumpet Performance (University of IA)-1987 · Bachelor of Arts Degree in Music Education (Midland University)-1983 Marla Janak BHHS Ambassador Real Estate 774 Olson Dr. Ste 105 Papillion, NE 68046

name: Lucy Schlafman
description: Your Real Estate Advisor! I live in Omaha since 1997. My passion is connecting with people from different cultures and developing friendships while sharing my multi-cultural background and life experiences. I truly believe there is a great real estate investment potential by bridging my resources across culture. I recognize and value the trust my clients have in me, and I strive everyday to exceed their expectations. I take great pride in my knowledge, loyalty, honesty, and ability to connect with clients to seamlessly execute transactions.

name: Conner Dana
description: Conner's passion is for helping his clients both sell and acquire commercial properties that will build wealth for them and their heirs. Income producing property is his specialty. Be that retail, industrial, multifamily, or office, his goal for Gemstone is to help investors buy and sell at the right time for the right price.

name: Laura Choi
description: As a Berkshire Hathaway HomeServices Ambassador Real Estate agent, I am dedicated to servicing our sellers and buyers. I am committed to maintaining an open line of communication, providing information on market data and trends, and creating that all-important trust. Weekly reports straight to you via email on buyers viewing your home. Neighborhood and market activity of what going on in the local and national real estate markets.

name: Meagan Wright-Geis
description: My goal is to bring a level of knowledge and dedication like none other to my clients. Having an understanding of what their wants and needs are, are always the priority, and I strive to bring that to the table in every way. I utilize the latest technologies, market research and business strategies to exceed your expectations. However, more importantly, I listen to and find solutions that are tailored specifically to you.

name: Amanda Sway
description: Amanda has been a real estate agent in the Omaha Metro since 2013. Amanda has helped over 425 families achieve their real estate goals, amounting to over $100 million worth of sales in her short career. She uses her experience, creativity, and knowledge to help her clients navigate through the ever changing real estate process. Amanda grew up on a farm in North Dakota. From an early age she was taught to work hard to get the end result she wanted. She attended NDSU and graduated with a B.S. in Business Admin. Having a degree has given her clients the added value of working with an agent who has more thorough understanding of Marketing, Management, and Financing.

name: Kaylie Beebe
description: Hi There! I'm Kaylie. Kaylie is a born and raised Nebraskan, mother, wife, and licensed realtor with 10 years of marketing and design background in her arsenal. She prides herself on being a patient, honest realtor with the belief that no question is a silly one. Whether you’re buying or selling, you have a guide, a line of defense, and a friend each step of the way + beyond. When Kaylie’s not selling real estate, she loves to spend time with her family, listen to music, make her daughter laugh, and dream up the next home reno project for her handy husband to tackle.

name: Lisa Harris
description: More about Lisa Meet Lisa Harris - one of Omaha’s top producers. Consistently ranked in the top 12% of all Berkshire Hathaway Home Services realtors in the US, Lisa has developed a keen aptitude stemming  from her sincere interest, knowledge and experience in the industry. Lisa understands what it is like to stand in her clients’ shoes. Relocating several times - buying and selling houses of her own - has afforded Lisa a sensitivity towards her clients’ journey, which can be attributed to the first-hand perspective she gained through her personal experience. Now, a longtime resident of the Omaha area and having raised her two daughters here, Lisa has gained a full understanding of the diverse needs of families in the community. Lisa specializes in all facets of the Real Estate business, whether it be navigating the way for first time homeowners, trying to land that perfect distressed property, or providing help in the luxury market, she knows and has experienced it all. Lisa is also certified as Residential Investment Specialist and owns several investment properties herself. She willingly shares all of her expertise with clients looking to diversify their investments with rental properties. Even with the sales, training and awards, Lisa simply wants you to enjoy the real estate process and have you win in the end. She has a true passion for exceeding your expectations from the moment you begin working together.

name: Matthew Feerhusen
description: Matt brings years of client-focused experience to all of his work.  Your needs, comfort, and ease will always be the focus. Matt’s flare for individualized design and style are the name of the game when helping you choose your perfect home! Whether it’s a primary residence, additional investment property, or commercial property, Matt is your trustworthy partner and expert Real Estate advisor. Reach out today to begin your exciting new Journey!

name: Dayna Gunter
description: Hi! I am a proud native of Omaha and believe that this community has made me the person I am today. I grew up camping, playing sports and enjoying the Henry Doorly Zoo. After high school, I attended Drake University and joined an amazing group of women in Alpha Phi Sorority. I moved to South Florida after college and enjoyed the beach life for 8 years. The great community of Omaha and my wonderful family were the reasons for me returning home. I started a family and have been loving the growth taking place in my city. As a Realtor, I am committed to educating, helping, and walking eager home buyers and sellers through the real estate process. My philosphy is to keep it fun, while paying close attention to the details. If you're looking for an agent that is dedicated to you and to keeping current on the market, then please reach out to me. It would be my pleasure to be your agent! I can't wait to chat with you. Find me on Instagram: @omaharealtordayna

name: Ria Zimmerman
description: Meet Ria Ria is a real estate broker with over 12 years of experience in multiple markets. She started her career by working with investors and asset management firms in the Philadelphia area. After becoming greatly knowledgeable in the field, she challenged herself to restart her career by moving to San Francisco. During her time there, she gained the valuable skills needed to thrive in a fast moving market. Equipped with extensive experience and sales strategies, Ria moved to the Scottsdale market to coach and develop 45+ agents.  Ria had the opportunity to build her own home in Omaha - her husband’s native city. Surrounded by family, Ria is thrilled to call Omaha her new home. Having been on both sides of the home buying process as a buyer and seller, Ria prides herself on providing unparalleled service to each client through her perseverance, integrity, empathy, and attention. While knowing that buying a home is a unique, important, and emotional process, Ria is eager to guide you in getting your dream home.

name: Natassia Rekte
description: Lifetime Lincolnite, I'm an active community member for many years now. Coming up on 10 years in the industry of real estate sales. I'm knowledged in the conveniences and key demographics in the variety of neighborhoods in Lincoln, and the city's growth. I drive my business with the three E's -- ethics, enthusiasm, and education for all of my clients. This has been especially helpful for my first-time homebuyer clients and relocating families and professionals. I absolutely love being a major player in the home buying and selling process. I care about all of my clients and I demonstrate that through my integrity and communication that remains beyond the sale. If you have a home to sell or if you're thinking about moving, contact me today.
